0at%20least%203%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20decision%20comes%20as%20researchers%20debate%20whether%20remote%20work%20and%20AI%20are%20curbing%20entry-level%20hiring.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20cause%2C%20landing%20that%20first%20job%20is%20getting%20tougher%20for%20many%20grads.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-important-new-job-economy-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estarting%20your%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20your%20boss%20might%20expect%20to%20see%20you%20in%20the%20office%20more%20often%20than%20your%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUK%20fintech%20company%20Revolut%20recently%20said%20that%2C%20starting%20in%202027%2C%20interns%20and%20participants%20in%20a%20program%20for%20recent%20grads%20will%20be%20expected%20to%20work%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20The%20company%20will%20continue%20to%20allow%20other%20employees%20to%20choose%20whether%20to%20work%20remotely%20or%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevolut%20says%20the%20change%20reflects%20the%20value%20of%20IRL%20learning%20for%20workers%20early%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20just%20learn%20from%20your%20manager%20telling%20you%20what%20to%20do.%20You%20actually%20observe%20how%20other%20people%20conduct%20their%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Queenie%20Li%2C%20the%20company's%20head%20of%20talent%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20broadly%20agree%20that%20early-career%20employees%20benefit%20from%20in-person%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-right-mentor-could-supercharge-your-career-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ementorship%20and%20informal%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20as%20firms%20like%20Revolut%20draw%20distinctions%20between%20junior%20and%20more%20experienced%20workers%2C%20labor%20market%20observers%20remain%20divided%20over%20the%20relative%20roles%20that%20remote%20work%2C%20AI%2C%20and%20other%20factors%20might%20play%20in%20employers'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwfh-bigger-driver-entry-level-job-woes-ai-researchers-say-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewillingness%20to%20hire%20entry-level%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20important%20question%20because%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20college%20graduates%20in%20their%20early%20to%20mid-20s%20typically%20had%20a%20lower%20unemployment%20rate%20than%20the%20overall%20workforce.%20That's%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%20Since%20late%202018%2C%20these%20workers%20have%20often%20faced%20a%20higher%20jobless%20rate%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorkfed.org%2Fresearch%2Fcollege-labor-market%23--%3Aexplore%3Aunemployment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20workforce%20as%20a%20whole%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20New%20York%20Federal%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3ba1bdf-ca4b-46b6-909b-e493e8599b0d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20remote-work%20effect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20John%20Lambert%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Warwick%2C%20and%20a%20colleague%20recently%20concluded%20that%20remote%20work%20better%20explains%20the%20decline%20in%20entry-level%20hiring%20than%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELambert%20and%20Yannick%20Schindler%20of%20the%20UK's%20Ellison%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20examined%20hiring%20and%20job-listing%20data%20across%20several%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20before%20and%20after%20the%20arrival%20of%20ChatGPT%20and%20the%20pandemic-driven%20shift%20to%20remote%20work.%20They%20found%20that%20the%20share%20of%20entry-level%20hires%20fell%20by%20as%20much%20as%2029%25%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20while%20hiring%20for%20senior%20positions%20rose%20by%20more%20than%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20it's%20easy%20to%20conflate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-search-networking-resume-early-career-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI's%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20that%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20Lambert%20said%2C%20is%20that%20both%20are%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-tools-software-engineers-workplace-paralysis-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edesk%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20be%20done%20from%20afar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELambert%20said%20remote%20work%20is%20the%20more%20likely%20reason%20for%20the%20drop%20in%20the%20entry-level%20share%20of%20new%20hires%20because%20the%20slowdown%20began%20before%20GenAI%20tools%20emerged%2C%20when%20the%20technology%20was%20still%20too%20limited%20to%20meaningfully%20affect%20hiring%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20when%20you%20compare%20these%20things%20jointly%20that%20you%20start%20to%20see%20a%20stronger%20relationship%20between%20work-from-home%20than%20generative%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20Fed%20researchers%20reached%20a%20similar%20conclusion%20on%20the%20effects%20of%20remote%20work.%20The%20setup%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20managers%20to%20train%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-young-remote-workers-miss-feedback-rto-wfh-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ementor%20new%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%20They%20studied%20an%20undisclosed%20Fortune%20500%20company%20and%20found%20that%20when%20colleagues%20are%20separated%2C%20%26quot%3Bfeedback%20tapers%20off%20dramatically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20loss%20in%20feedback%20is%20more%20pronounced%20for%20younger%20workers%2C%20who%20miss%20out%20on%20constructive%20comments%20that%20spur%20their%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20who%20studies%20remote%20work%20sees%20it%20as%20such%20a%20cut-and-dried%20explanation.%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20said%20that%20remote%20work%2C%20AI%2C%20pandemic-era%20learning%20losses%2C%20and%20a%20broader%20hiring%20slowdown%20that's%20been%20particularly%20hard%20on%20tech%20jobs%20are%20all%20plausible%20explanations%20for%20the%20weak%20job%20market%20for%20college%20graduates.%20Yet%2C%20Bloom%20said%2C%20current%20data%20can't%20determine%20which%20factors%20are%20driving%20the%20trend%20or%20by%20how%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d2c083b-8e67-402d-b852-a03300a2c2d9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20AI%20effect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20research%2C%20Mark%20Ma%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20found%20that%20companies%20with%20AI%20in%20job%20titles%20or%20job%20descriptions%20reduced%20overall%20hiring%2C%20with%20the%20biggest%20declines%20in%20early-career%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMa%20said%20that%20suggests%20that%20as%20firms%20ramp%20up%20spending%20on%20AI%20or%20hire%20workers%20with%20AI%20skills%2C%20they%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-grads-class-of-2026-job-searching-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efewer%20entry-level%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20getting%20rid%20of%20these%20junior%20positions%20because%20the%20junior-level%20work%20could%20be%20more%20easily%20replaced%20by%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMa%20said%20that%20because%20remote%20work%20rates%20were%20higher%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20than%20they%20are%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-new-grads-can-stand-out-in-slow-job-market-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecent%20grads%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20have%20had%20a%20tougher%20time%20then%20than%20they%20do%20today.%20Yet%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20problem%20is%20getting%20worse%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20firms%20with%20more%20remote%20job%20postings%20increased%2C%20rather%20than%20reduced%2C%20hiring%20for%20junior%20positions%20overall%2C%20Ma%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20firms%20are%20actually%20growing%20faster%2C%20so%20they%20need%20to%20hire%20more%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dfae8889-a091-41ce-a409-e7177f95c291%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20learning%20happen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20do%20get%20jobs%2C%20many%20welcome%20at%20least%20some%20in-person%20work.%20A%202025%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F692675%2Ffully-remote-work-least-popular-gen-z.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20only%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20who%20could%20do%20their%20jobs%20remotely%20wanted%20to%20do%20so%20full%20time%2C%20compared%20with%20about%20one-third%20of%20older%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20setups%2C%20where%20workers%20spend%20at%20least%20part%20of%20the%20time%20in%20the%20office%2C%20can%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20medium%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20effective%20way%20to%20ensure%20early-career%20workers%20get%20the%20mentorship%20they%20need%20and%20often%20say%20they%20want%2C%20said%20Brad%20Hershbein%2C%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20W.E.%20Upjohn%20Institute%20for%20Employment%20Research%2C%20a%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemote%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20early%20in%20their%20careers%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20necessarily%20pick%20up%20on%20all%20the%20things%20that%20will%20make%20them%20as%20productive%20unless%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-often-are-you-going-to-office-take-survey-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20witness%20them%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20end%20up%20being%20unhappy%20because%20they're%20just%20not%20learning%20some%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Hershbein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20learning%20happen%20was%20part%20of%20what%20drove%20the%20thinking%20behind%20Revolut's%20in-office%20requirement%20for%20interns%20and%20some%20early-career%20workers%2C%20Li%20said.%20The%20firm%20plans%20to%20bring%20on%20about%20500%20interns%20and%20graduate-program%20participants%20in%202027%2C%20up%20from%20about%20300%20this%20year%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-ai-entry-level-hiring-new-grads-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783244522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4692c6e3bd3a50082bf9f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-ai-entry-level-hiring-new-grads-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Why%20are%20recent%20grads%20struggling%20to%20find%20jobs%3F%20Researchers%20debate%20whether%20remote%20work%20or%20AI%20are%20driving%20a%20decline%20in%20entry-level%20hiring.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Uber's%20insurance%20and%20operational%20fees%20can%20vary%20widely%20on%20similar%20trips%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-white%20Uber%20banner%20hangs%20over%20the%20columns%20at%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20building.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a466b492680585ce91a3b83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224427%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUber%20charges%20fees%20for%20insurance%20and%20%26quot%3Boperational%20costs%26quot%3B%20on%20every%20trip.%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUber's%20insurance%20and%20operational%20fees%20are%20among%20the%20biggest%20costs%20baked%20into%20a%20fare%20on%20the%20app.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20study%20found%20they%20can%20vary%20a%20lot%20between%20very%20similar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-pricing-report-finds-fare-differences-2026-6%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20trips%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUber%20says%20it%20collects%20%26quot%3Boverall%20insurance%20and%20operational%20expenses%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20determining%20the%20cost%20of%20individual%20trips.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20charges%20riders%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20fee%20for%20insurance%20and%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20harder%20to%20predict%20than%20the%20price%20you'll%20pay%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20the%20overall%20trip%2C%20a%20new%20study%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELen%20Sherman%2C%20an%20executive%20in%20residence%20and%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-into-columbia-business-school-advice-from-admissions-alumni%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EColumbia%20Business%20School%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20analyzed%20120%20Uber%20Reserve%20trips%20completed%20by%20one%20driver%20between%20Ithaca%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20an%20airport%20in%20Syracuse%20over%20a%20two-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trips%20were%20similar%20in%20several%20ways%2C%20Sherman%20said.%20Each%20was%20driven%20by%20the%20same%20driver%20in%20the%20same%20Tesla%20Model%20Y.%20Each%20also%20followed%20essentially%20the%20same%20route%20along%20the%20freeway%2C%20covered%20nearly%20identical%20distances%2C%20and%20began%20and%20ended%20at%20similar%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20roughly%2060-mile%20trips%2C%20Uber's%20reported%20commercial%20auto%20insurance%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20operational%20charge%20on%20each%20ride%20ranged%20from%20%2413.75%20to%20%2450%20%E2%80%94%20an%20interesting%20result%2C%20Sherman%20said%2C%20given%20how%20similar%20the%20trips%20were%20from%20a%20risk%20standpoint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20identical%20trips%20by%20the%20same%20driver%2C%20the%20same%20car%2C%20and%20the%20same%20route%20in%20the%20same%20distance%2C%20there%20should%20not%20be%20a%20much%20higher%20variation%20in%20what%20you%20say%20your%20commercial%20insurance%20costs%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20fee%20covers%20government-mandated%20insurance%20for%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fee%20can%20vary%20due%20to%20multiple%20factors%2C%20%26quot%3Bincluding%20the%20trip's%20origin%20city%20and%20distance%2C%20duration%2C%20time%20of%20day%2C%20and%20weather%2C%20and%20is%20included%20in%20the%20price%20you%20see%20in%20the%20Uber%20app%20before%20requesting%20a%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229660350d-63c3-4a95-937d-de3f99ec91a3%5C%22%3EInsurance%20accounts%20for%20one-fifth%20of%20the%20average%20ride-hailing%20fare%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20has%20long%20said%20that%20rider%20prices%20and%20driver%20earnings%20can%20change%20based%20on%20demand.%20The%20variation%20in%20insurance%20and%20operational%20fees%20in%20the%20study%2C%20though%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Btwice%20as%20high%20as%20the%20variance%20in%20price%2C%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20share%20of%20each%20fare%20that%20Uber%20keeps%2C%20Sherman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20says%20it%20relies%20on%20a%20mix%20of%20third-party%20insurance%20and%20self-insurance%20%E2%80%94%20setting%20aside%20cash%20to%20cover%20potential%20accidents%20or%20other%20claims%20%E2%80%94%20in%20its%20ride-hailing%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriven-for-uber-decade-dont-know-what-my-future-holds-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERide-hailing%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esee%20how%20much%20Uber%20charges%20for%20insurance%20and%20operations%20on%20each%20ride%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20going%20into%20the%20details%20on%20a%20trip%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20their%20weekly%20earnings%20roundups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20says%20in%20the%20breakdown%20that%20the%20insurance%20and%20operational%20fee%20is%20an%20estimate%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20reflect%20insurance%20expenses%20incurred%20on%20individual%20trips%20but%20goes%20toward%20overall%20insurance%20and%20operational%20expenses%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20screenshots%20of%20such%20roundups%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20It%20does%20not%20detail%20what%20counts%20as%20an%20operational%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20about%2021%25%20of%20each%20rider's%20fare%20on%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20goes%20toward%20insurance%20costs%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20released%20this%20week%20by%20Gridwise%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20helps%20gig%20workers%20track%20their%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2053%25%20goes%20to%20the%20driver%2C%20while%2015%25%20goes%20to%20the%20app.%20Gridwise%20analyzed%20data%20from%20trips%20completed%20during%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Faverage-homeowners-insurance-cost%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EInsurance%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20ride-hailing%20companies%20are%20falling%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20US%2C%20Gridwise%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Western%20US%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20a%20fare%20that%20ride-hailing%20companies%20set%20aside%20for%20insurance%20fell%20nearly%2021%25%20between%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202025%20and%20the%20same%20period%20in%202026%2C%20according%20to%20Gridwise.%20The%20savings%20came%20after%20California%20reduced%20insurance%20requirements%20at%20the%20start%20of%202026%2C%20Gridwise%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20same%20period%2C%20ride-hailing%20companies%20raised%20platform%20fees%20and%20cut%20some%20rider%20prices%2C%20while%20raising%20driver%20pay%201.2%25%20on%20average%2C%20said%20Brandon%20Sellers%2C%20Gridwise's%20vice%20president%20of%20marketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVery%2C%20very%2C%20very%20little%20of%20that%20went%20to%20driver%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20Sellers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20Uber%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20808-854-4501.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere's%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eguide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-insurance-fees-varied-widely-in-similar-rides-study-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783244521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a466b5a1aaffe3020cb28c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-insurance-fees-varied-widely-in-similar-rides-study-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Uber's%20insurance%20charges%20can%20vary%20greatly%2C%20affecting%20what%20riders%20pay%2C%20reveals%20Columbia's%20Len%20Sherman.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20got%20this%20lawyer%20away%20from%20his%20desk%3A%20'Dramatically%20more%20efficient'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Claude%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fc9f44c9dd4cb81cda80f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECorporate%20attorney%20Zack%20Shapiro%20primarily%20uses%20Anthropic's%20Claude.%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Boivin%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20corporate%20attorney%20says%20his%20use%20of%20AI%20at%20work%20has%20made%20his%20life%20so%20much%20better.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZack%20Shapiro%20founded%20the%20AI-native%20law%20firm%20Rains%20and%20uses%20the%20tech%20to%20automate%20grunt%20work%20tasks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20making%20me%20dramatically%20more%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20Shapiro%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20attorney%20Zack%20Shapiro%20used%20to%20spend%20hours%20each%20workday%20stuck%20behind%20his%20desk%20drafting%20legal%20documents%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-word%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20Word%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20managing%20partner%20of%20the%20boutique%20AI-native%20law%20firm%20Rains%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-terms-definitions-glossary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20fundamentally%20changed%20how%20he%20practices%20law%20%E2%80%94%20freeing%20him%20from%20much%20of%20the%20tedious%20work%20and%20even%20getting%20him%20out%20from%20behind%20his%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20making%20me%20dramatically%20more%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20Shapiro%20told%20Business%20Insider%20la