%20in%20the%20products%20they%20build.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20have%20fewer%20workers%2C%20more%20technical%20talent%2C%20and%20a%20flatter%20management%20structure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20is%20for%20the%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20new%20working%20paper%2C%20researchers%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20and%20the%20nonprofit%20business%20school%2C%20INSEAD%2C%20found%20that%20AI-native%20startups%20are%20building%20smaller%2C%20flatter%20teams%20with%20fewer%20entry-level%20workers%20than%20their%20non-AI%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BAI-Native%20Firms%2C%26quot%3B%20examined%20Y%20Combinator%20startups%20from%202020%20to%202024%20and%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20US%20venture-backed%20startups%20whose%20first%20financing%20closed%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20defines%20a%20new%20category%20of%20%26quot%3BAI-native%20startups%26quot%3B%20characterized%20by%20two%20shifts%20in%20productivity.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20process%20channel%3A%20They%20use%20AI%20inside%20the%20company%20to%20make%20employees%20more%20productive%2C%20such%20as%20helping%20them%20code%2C%20sell%2C%20design%2C%20or%20coordinate%20work%20faster.%20The%20second%20is%20the%20product%20channel%3A%20They%20embed%20AI%20directly%20into%20what%20the%20company%20sells%2C%20so%20customers%20can%20use%20the%20product%20to%20perform%20work%20that%20once%20required%20human%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI-native%20startups%20are%2025%25%20smaller%2C%20with%20about%2013%25%20more%20engineers%2C%20and%20their%20shares%20of%20entry-level%20workers%20and%20managers%20are%20each%20roughly%2015%25%20lower%20than%20non-AI-native%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20test%20a%20broadly%20accepted%20premise%20of%20the%20AI%20boom%3A%20AI%20is%20reshaping%20the%20bottom%20rungs%20of%20the%20career%20ladder.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-is-raising-bar-for-entry-level-employees-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEntry-level%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20using%20it%20to%20take%20on%20bigger%20responsibilities%20sooner%20and%20automate%20routine%20tasks.%20This%20comes%20as%20vibecoding%20has%20also%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20non-engineers%20to%20turn%20ideas%20into%20prototypes%2C%20blurring%20the%20threshold%20and%20need%20for%20technical%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20paper%20found%20that%20the%20AI%20is%20creating%20a%20greater%20demand%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-training-employees-for-ai-workplace-learning-agents-big-four-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexpert-level%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20share%20of%20senior%20workers%20at%20AI-native%20startups%20is%2020%25%20higher%2C%20and%20these%20companies%20tend%20to%20attract%20a%20specific%20type%20of%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI-tagged%20firms%20employ%20smaller%20teams%20of%20more%20talented%20and%20technical%20workers.%20These%20workers%20are%20especially%20likely%20to%20be%20graduates%20from%20elite%20institutions%2C%20concentrated%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20and%20male%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20suggests%20AI-native%20startups%20may%20not%20be%20democratizing%20access%20to%20opportunities%20so%20much%20as%20concentrating%20opportunity%20among%20already-credentialed%2C%20highly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-google-employees-leaving-quitting-big-tech-ai-startup-careers-2026-6%2527%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etechnical%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors'%20bigger%20concern%20is%20how%20that%20will%20affect%20demographic%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20AI%20tools%20accelerate%20learning%20for%20those%20who%20use%20them%2C%20differential%20adoption%20rates%20may%20translate%20into%20widening%20performance%20gaps%20%E2%80%94%20both%20for%20individual%20workers%20within%20firms%20and%20for%20the%20entrepreneurs%20who%20found%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startups-entry-level-workers-jobs-careers-harvard-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783242182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a495c5fe3bd3a50082c04ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startups-entry-level-workers-jobs-careers-harvard-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI-native%20startups%20are%20running%20smaller%2C%20flatter%20teams%20and%20are%20hiring%20more%20senior%20talent%20rather%20than%20entry-level%20talent%2C%20a%20Harvard%20study%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40businessinsider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20multi-millionaire%20left%20NYC%20for%2025%20years.%20Now%20he's%20back%20and%20ready%20to%20pay%20more%20taxes.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andy%20Tobias%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4681611bba93485607acb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Tobias%20in%20his%20Manhattan%20apartment.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Tobias%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnumber-millionaires-billionaires-nyc-singapore-bay-area-henley-migration-sf-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20City%20millionaire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20will%20happily%20pay%20more%20taxes.%20Just%20make%20sure%20to%20send%20him%20a%20fruit%20basket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20financial%20writer%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Patriotic%20Millionaires%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group%20of%20high-net-worth%20Americans%20who%20crusade%20for%20higher%20taxes%20on%20the%20wealthy.%20He%20said%20he%20would%20not%20mind%20paying%20them%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20which%20he%20said%20is%20a%20city%20%26quot%3Bworth%20supporting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Mayor%20Zohran%20Mamdani's%20key%20campaign%20promises%20was%20to%20raise%20taxes%20on%20the%20wealthy%20to%20help%20bridge%20the%20city's%20budget%20gap%20and%20use%20that%20money%20for%20free%20buses%20and%20universal%20childcare.%20In%20May%2C%20state%20lawmakers%20passed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgov-kathy-hochul-zohran-mamdani-tax-billionaires-nyc-second-homes-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epied-%C3%A0-terre%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20spearheaded%20by%20Mamdani%2C%20that%20more%20than%20doubled%20property%20taxes%20on%20second%20homes%20valued%20at%20over%20%245%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20wealthy%20New%20Yorkers%20are%20not%20on%20board.%20Citadel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fken-griffin-pay-mamdani-nyc-pied-a-terre-tax-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20Ken%20Griffin%20denounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20new%20policy%20after%20Mamdani%20filmed%20a%20video%20announcing%20the%20tax%20in%20front%20of%20Griffin's%20New%20York%20City%20penthouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tax%20itself%20is%20a%20tax%20that%20discriminates%20against%20a%20narrow%20group%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20CNBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229489%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andy%20Tobias%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4681e71bba93485607acbe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226326%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20%26quot%3BNo%20Kings%20in%20America%26quot%3B%20sign%20inside%20Andrew%20Tobias's%20apartment.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tobias%20agrees%20with%20Mamdani%20that%20the%20ultrawealthy%20should%20pay%20more%20taxes%2C%20he%20said%20that%20these%20wealthy%20taxpayers%20should%20be%20celebrated%2C%20not%20vilified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Mayor%20should%20send%20the%20ultra-wealthy%20taxpayers%20a%20thank-you%20note%20and%20a%20fruit%20basket%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20are%20successful%20and%20pay%20a%20lot%20of%20taxes%20should%2C%20first%20of%20all%2C%20be%20celebrated%2C%20and%20respected%2C%20and%20probably%20thanked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETobias%20is%20one%20of%20several%20New%20Yorkers%20Business%20Insider%20interviewed%20as%20part%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fcost-of-the-city%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECost%20of%20the%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%2C%20which%20looks%20to%20understand%20how%20people%20across%20the%20five%20boroughs%20get%20by%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20cities%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb1d7554-74d8-41d8-a7f5-de4f9afd0c0d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20a%20multimillionaire%20makes%20and%20spends%20his%20money%20in%20NYC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2079-year-old%20writer%2C%20who%20winters%20in%20Miami%2C%20gained%20his%20fortune%20after%20publishing%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Only%20Investment%20Guide%20You'll%20Ever%20Need%26quot%3B%20in%201978%20and%20launching%20Managing%20Your%20Money%2C%20a%20personal%20finance%20software%20application%2C%20in%201984.%20He%20also%20benefited%20from%20property%20investments%20he%20bought%20in%20Miami%20in%20the%20mid-1980s%20and%20sold%20about%2020%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETobias%20made%20a%20living%20by%20giving%20investment%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhsbc-head-of-wealth-personal-banking-shares-most-important-advice-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advice%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20people%20through%20the%20written%20word.%20He%20wrote%20articles%20and%20columns%20for%20multiple%20magazines%2C%20including%20Esquire%2C%20Time%2C%20and%20Playboy%2C%20and%20published%2012%20books%20%E2%80%94%20three%20that%20became%20New%20York%20Times%20best-sellers.%20He%20is%20also%20well%20known%20for%20his%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Best%20Little%20Boy%20in%20the%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20originally%20published%20under%20a%20pseudonym%20in%201973%2C%20that%20recounts%20his%20experiences%20growing%20up%20gay%20in%20the%201950s%2C%2060s%20and%2070s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20he%20splits%20his%20time%20in%20New%20York%20between%20his%20beach%20house%20on%20Fire%20Island%20and%20his%20Upper%20West%20Side%20apartment%2C%20which%20he%20bought%20in%201977%20for%20%2411%2C000%20in%20cash%20plus%20a%20%2430%2C000%20mortgage.%20Today%2C%20he%20estimates%20the%20apartment%20is%20worth%20around%20%242.5%20million.%20He%20also%20owns%20four%20apartments%20in%20Miami%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20him%20and%20the%20other%20three%20for%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20one%20of%20the%20very%20fortunate%20people%20who%20can%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20New%20York%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20receives%20a%20monthly%20%243%2C360%20check%20from%20Social%20Security%2C%20%246%2C600%20a%20month%20from%20a%20charitable%20gift%20annuity%2C%20an%20annual%20royalty%20check%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Btakes%20a%20few%20hundred%20thousand%20dollars%20a%20year%26quot%3B%20from%20his%20IRA.%20Every%20other%20year%2C%20he%20also%20gets%20a%20check%20from%20reruns%20of%20his%20appearances%20on%20The%20Tonight%20Show%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-popular-comedians-of-all-time-2018-4%231986-joan-rivers-24%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJohnny%20Carson%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20the%20last%20one%20he%20got%20was%20for%2038%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-media-container%3D%5C%22image%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22img%5C%22%20data-e2e-na