able%20to%20give%20it%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228aabc4f1-b009-4106-ba38-9e56f31bdada%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaying%20taxes%20in%20NYC%20hasn't%20always%20been%20smooth%20sailing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETobias%20was%20born%20in%20Lenox%20Hill%20Hospital%20on%20the%20Upper%20East%20Side.%20He%20came%20from%20an%20upper-middle-class%20family%2C%20with%20a%20father%20who%20worked%20as%20an%20advertising%20executive%20and%20a%20mother%20from%20whom%20he%20inherited%20the%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20gene.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20one%20really%20smart%20thing%20I've%20done%20in%20my%20life%20is%20my%20choice%20in%20parents%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20briefly%20lived%20in%20Cambridge%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20while%20completing%20his%20undergraduate%20degree%20in%20Slavic%20languages%20and%20literatures%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-student-struggled-find-internship-worried-job-market-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvard%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20later%20on%20his%20MBA%20at%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tobias%20today%20supports%20higher%20taxes%20on%20wealthy%20people%20like%20himself%2C%20he%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20city%20in%20the%201980s%20after%20a%20tax%20dispute%20with%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Department%20of%20Finance.%20The%20department%20wanted%20to%20charge%20him%20unincorporated%20business%20taxes%20for%20work%20he%20had%20been%20doing%20as%20a%20writer%20and%20speaker%20outside%20New%20York%2C%20which%20Tobias%20argued%20was%20absurd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20read%20all%20their%20definition%20of%20who's%20a%20business%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20wasn't%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-media-container%3D%5C%22image%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22img%5C%22%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-figure-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-content-type%3D%5C%22image%2Fjpeg%5C%22%20data-srcs%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bhttps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a468255e3bd3a50082bf917%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3BcontentType%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bimage%2Fjpeg%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioW%26quot%3B%3A4160%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioH%26quot%3B%3A5200%7D%7D%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a468255e3bd3a50082bf917%3Fwidth%3D1300%26format%3Djpeg%26auto%3Dwebp%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andy%20Tobias%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-caption%5C%22%3E%5CnAndrew%20Tobias%20in%20his%20Manhattan%20apartment.%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-source%5C%22%3E%5CnCorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20didn't%20make%20sense%20to%20pay%20the%20unincorporated%20business%20tax%20for%20%26quot%3Bthe%20privilege%20of%20doing%20business%20in%20the%20city%20of%20New%20York%26quot%3B%20when%20giving%20a%20speech%20in%20Utah%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20threatened%20that%20if%20they%20made%20him%20pay%20the%20tax%2C%20he%20would%20permanently%20move%20to%20Miami%2C%20spending%20six%20months%20there%20a%20year%20and%20costing%20New%20York%20City%20all%20the%20taxes%20he%20was%20already%20paying.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20he%20paid%20the%20tax%20and%20changed%20his%20permanent%20residence%20to%20Miami.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20matter%20of%20manhood.%20Having%20made%20that%20threat%2C%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20to%20follow%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20leave%20because%20of%20the%20money%2C%20I%20left%20because%20they%20made%20me%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20used%20the%20extra%20money%20he%20saved%20from%20not%20paying%20New%20York%20City%20taxes%20to%20give%20away%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fgifts%2Fcompanies-that-give-back%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echaritable%20causes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20take%20that%20same%20money%20and%20give%20it%20away%20instead%20to%20worthy%20causes%20that%20I%20chose%20was%20such%20a%20better%20feeling%20than%20having%20it%20taken%2C%26quot%3B%20Tobias%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20I%20gave%20that%20money%20to%20whatever%20cause%20it%20was%2C%20I%20would%20get%20a%20wonderful%20thank%20you%20note%20%E2%80%94%20which%20wasn't%20the%20reason%20I%20gave%20it%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20just%20makes%20you%20feel%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20his%20fruit%20basket%20analogy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-new-york-city-miami-back-got-too-expensive-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMiami%20was%20no%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%2025%20years%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20New%20York%20to%20be%20close%20to%20his%20loved%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20decided%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20worry%20about%20how%20many%20days%20I%20spent%20where%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20close%20to%20important%20people%20in%20my%20life%20who%20were%20dying%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20started%20paying%20New%20York%20taxes%20again%20nearly%2020%20years%20ago.%20I%20don't%20mind%3A%20it's%20a%20great%20city.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20still%20spends%20the%20winters%20in%20Miami%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20year%20he%20splits%20his%20time%20between%20his%20Manhattan%20apartment%20and%20his%20beach%20house%20on%20Fire%20Island%2C%20a%20residence%20he%20said%20had%20%26quot%3Bmore%20happiness%20per%20square%20foot.%26quot%3B%20Although%20taxes%20are%20high%2C%20he%20said%20he%20can%20afford%20them%20and%20would%20not%20live%20anywhere%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3f6e951-a879-41d5-aac9-dc1eb21636fe%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrugal%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20extravagant%20in%20others%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETobias%20considers%20himself%20%26quot%3Bfrugal%26quot%3B%20in%20some%20aspects.%20He%20does%20not%20own%20a%20car%2C%20takes%20public%20transportation%2C%20and%20refuses%20to%20waste%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20my%20hobbies%20is%20eating%20expired%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20some%20salad%20dressing%20that's%20older%20than%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20never%20had%20kids%2C%20a%20therapist%2C%20or%20any%20big%20medical%20bills%20to%20add%20to%20his%20regular%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20likes%20to%20spend%20his%20money%20on%20is%20unique%20pieces%20of%20documented%20history%2C%20eccentricities%2C%20and%20art.%20His%20apartment%20walls%20are%20lined%20with%20lithographs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-yorker-cartoon-working-women-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20Yorker%20comics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20signed%20historical%20documents%2C%20like%20the%20Presidential%20Pride%20Proclamation%20signed%20by%20President%20Bill%20Clinton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andy%20Tobias%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46cb2ce3bd3a50082bfd54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Tobias%20standing%20next%20to%20New%20Yorker%20cartoons%20displayed%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20his%20apartment.%3Cp%3ECarrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20crazy%20person's%20apartment%2C%20but%20I%20love%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETobias%20considers%20himself%20very%20lucky.%20He%20travels%20to%20Europe%20every%20May%2C%20splurges%20on%20dinners%20with%20friends%2C%20and%20was%20able%20to%20