LC.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20truck%20driving%2C%20I%20only%20had%20a%20CB%20radio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20telephone%2C%20no%20communications%2C%20and%20no%20technology%20for%20anybody%20to%20know%20where%20I%20parked%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEspecially%20as%20a%20woman%2C%20I%20thought%20about%20things%20like%20whether%20I%20was%20parked%20in%20a%20safe%20place.%20If%20I%20didn't%20move%20my%20truck%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20how%20is%20somebody%20going%20to%20know%20whether%20something's%20happened%20to%20me%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20AI%20and%20other%20technology%20can%20tell%20me%20if%20there's%20a%20deer%20in%20front%20of%20me.%20It%20can%20tell%20me%20if%20one%20of%20my%20drivers%20is%20dozing%20off%20or%20daydreaming.%20It%20can%20remind%20me%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20has%20gotten%20to%20a%20point%20where%20I'm%20accepting%20of%20it.%20It%20can%20help%20prevent%20what%20could%20go%20wrong%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuild-america-act-autonomous-trucking-remote-workers-training-program-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAutonomous%20trucks%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20different.%20I'm%20open%20to%20the%20conversation.%20But%20until%20it%20can%20prove%20to%20me%20that%20there%20will%20not%20be%20any%20type%20of%20loss%20of%20life%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e3b25c0-7c14-4cb4-ac7f-99e97a4b939e%5C%22%3ETruck%20drivers%20were%20their%20own%20patrol%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20from%20Boone%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20and%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-college-truck-driver-job-salary-no-regret-debt-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edriving%20trucks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201979.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20truck%20was%20a%20'79%20Diamond%20Reo.%20Once%20I%20got%20a%20taste%20of%20going%20to%20different%20places%20and%20experiencing%20different%20cultures%2C%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%2080%2C000%20pounds%20of%20iron.%20My%20haul%20has%20included%20cows%2C%20steel%2C%20produce%2C%20and%20dynamite.%20The%20last%20time%20I%20counted%2C%20I%20had%205.7%20million%20safe%20driving%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20truck.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46f95b65e65d39ff1c94dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22405%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIngrid%20Brown%20by%20her%20truck%20in%202002.%3Cp%3EIngrid%20Brown%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20safety%20really%20depended%20on%20the%20person%20behind%20the%20wheel.%20It%20depended%20on%20how%20well%20you%20did%20pre-trips%20or%20safety%20inspections%20before%20you%20hit%20the%20road.%20It%20depended%20on%20how%20well%20you%20chose%20to%20drive%2C%20how%20well%20you%20understood%20the%20hours%20you%20should%20be%20running%2C%20and%20how%20many%20hours%20you%20actually%20physically%20can%20run%20to%20keep%20everything%20safe.%20You%20were%20your%20own%20patrol.%20You%20were%20your%20own%20self-discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20we%20had%20rules.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20followed%20designated%20hours%20of%20service.%20But%20that%20was%20partly%20on%20you.%20You%20logged%20your%20hours%20on%20paper.%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20back%20then%2C%20I%20may%20have%20rewritten%20the%20life%20of%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20only%20had%20each%20other%20to%20rely%20on.%20That's%20how%20we%20learned%20this%20business.%20There%20was%20no%20technology%20to%20say%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22279807a2-3b95-45c9-9a77-cfc67b6ec51e%5C%22%3EThe%20phone%20changed%20my%20whole%20world%20of%20safety%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20piece%20of%20technology%20that%20really%20changed%20my%20job%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-history-of-the-cellphone-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20connection%20to%20me.%20I%20would%20call%20to%20get%20directions.%20I%20would%20call%20to%20see%20if%20my%20appointment%20time%20was%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20something%20went%20bad%2C%20that%20phone%20was%20there%20for%20me%20to%20call%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I've%20got%20this%20load%20on%20me.%20I'm%20in%20traffic.%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%2030%20minutes%20late.%26quot%3B%20And%20the%20time%20saved%20was%20unreal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20all%20about%20adapting.%20I%20was%20never%20a%20computer%20girl%20because%20I'm%20a%20'61%20baby%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20letting%20myself%20fall%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20resistance%20to%20technology%20was%20with%20Motive%2C%20a%20fleet%20technology%20company%2C%20back%20when%20it%20was%20still%20KeepTruckin.%20The%20company%20provides%20electronic%20logs%2C%20tracking%2C%20maintenance%2C%20driver%20coaching%2C%20and%20AI-powered%20dashcam%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20monitored.%20Nobody%20needs%20to%20know%20when%20I%20stopped%20to%20go%20to%20the%20bathroom.%20I%20didn't%20want%20someone%20telling%20me%20how%20to%20do%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20on%2C%20I%20found%20it%20to%20be%20a%20good%20helpmate.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20off%20me.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20sit%20up%20during%20my%20breaks%20to%20do%20paperwork.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20camera%20system%20also%20protects%20drivers%20when%20things%20happen%20because%20it%20tells%20the%20true%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20kind%20of%20technology%20I%20look%20for.%20I%20don't%20just%20want%20to%20know%20what%20went%20wrong%20before.%20I%20want%20something%20that's%20going%20to%20prevent%20something%20from%20going%20wrong%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7a9b44d-4514-49a6-a504-eb83517aa4c5%5C%22%3EI'm%20still%20watching%20autonomous%20trucks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20with%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-on-autonomy-robotaxis-self-driving-nuro-kodiak-waabi-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautonomous%20trucking%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they've%20come%20to%20me%20as%20a%20sounding%20board%20to%20ask%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20some%20questions%20too%2C%20before%20I%20can%20give%20my%20full%20opinion%20on%20autonomous%20trucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20say%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20unpredictability%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-truck-drivers-struggle-with-low-wages-long-hours-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etruck%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20accustomed%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20see%20a%20car%20half%20a%20mile%20or%20a%20mile%20in%20front%20of%20me%2C%20and%20I%20can%20watch%20it%20and%20predict%20what%20it%20might%20do.%20If%20he%20turns%20left%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20slow%20down%20prior%20to%20that.%20If%20he%20turns%20right%2C%20I%20can%20move%20left%20way%20ahead%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20been%20shown%20yet%20that%20an%20autonomous%20truck%20can%20do%20that%20before%20a%20situation%20is%20already%20in%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20want%20to%20learn%20more.%20My%20experience%20with%20other%20technology%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20need%20to%20quit%20being%20closed-minded%20because%20I%20could%20be%20missing%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20world%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-walmart-make-fully-driverless-delivery-truck-front-seat-video-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautonomous%20trucking%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20validated%2C%20I%20could%20see%20them%20handling%20local%20hauls%20or%20short-run%20jobs.%20As%20far%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-to-be-female-long-haul-truck-driver-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong%20hauls%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'll%20gladly%20stay%20behind%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20I've%20been%20a%20trucker%20for%20almost%2047%20years.%20I've%20got%20employees%20who%20drive%20the%20trucks%20I%20run%2C%20and%20I%20still%20drive%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20see%20people%20who%20have%20lived%20their%20lives%20and%20are%20giving%20their%20lives%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-truckers-salaries-wages-drop-deregulation-1980s-industry-problem-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrucking%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20go%20without%20a%20paycheck%20because%20somebody%20created%20something%20they%20think%20is%20bigger%20and%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20I'm%20talking%20about%20the%20empathy%2C%20the%20thought%2C%20the%20concern%2C%20and%20the%20care.%20Why%20would%20you%20want%20to%20take%20people's%20jobs%20away%20from%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETruckers%20don't%20need%20to%20go%20anywhere.%20They%20need%20the%20tools%20and%20the%20help%2C%20along%20with%20what%20they%20already%20have%20within%20themselves%2C%20to%20make%20sure%20every%20single%20person%20around%20them%20is%20as%20safe%20as%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fveteran-trucker-ai-safer-autonomous-trucks-not-ready-ingrid-brown-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783240861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46e5191bba93485607b23b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fveteran-trucker-ai-safer-autonomous-trucks-not-ready-ingrid-brown-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ingrid%20Brown%2C%20a%20trucker%20of%2047%20years%2C%20said%20technology%20like%20the%20cellphone%20and%20AI%20has%20made%20truck%20driving%20safer%20but%20autonomous%20trucks%20still%20need%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20Patriotism%20vs%20Partisan%20Politics%20Goof-Up%20At%20US%20250th%20Birthday%20Celebrations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20leaned%20into%20partisan%20territory%20unusual%20for%20an%20Independence%20Day%20address%2C%20which%20presidents%20typically%20use%20as%20a%20moment%20to%20unify%20the%20country.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783240786000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-250th-anniversary-july-4-celebrations-president-donald-trumps-patriotism-vs-partisan-politics-goof-up-at-us-250th-birthday-celebrations-11729238%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20leaned%20into%20partisan%20territory%20unusual%20for%20an%20Independence%20Day%20address%2C%20which%20presidents%20typically%20use%20as%20a%20moment%20to%20unify%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-250th-anniversary-july-4-celebrations-president-donald-trumps-patriotism-vs-partisan-politics-goof-up-at-us-250th-birthday-celebrations-11729238%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-250th-anniversary-july-4-celebrations-president-donald-trumps-patriotism-vs-partisan-politics-goof-up-at-us-250th-birthday-celebrations-11729238%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-250th-anniversary-july-4-celebrations-president-donald-trumps-patriotism-vs-partisan-politics-goof-up-at-us-250th-birthday-celebrations-11729238%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20every%20job%20description%20suddenly%20feels%20like%20a%20CVS%20receipt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20a%20dress%20shirt%20and%20black%20tie%20holds%20a%20very%20long%20printed%20job%20description.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4694ef1bba93485607add5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Robin%20Olsen%20started%20applying%20for%20communications%20jobs%20three%20months%20ago%2C%20she%20noticed%20a%20shift%3A%20The%20job%20descriptions%20had%20grown%20longer.%20One%20combined%20communications%20and%20marketing%2C%20typically%20two%20separate%20roles%2C%20into%20one.%20Others%20seemed%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20wish%20lists%2C%26quot%3B%20Olsen%20says.%20One%20was%20so%20overwhelmingly%20long%20that%20it%20prompted%20Olsen%20to%20shut%20it%20from%20her%20browser.%20%26quot%3BMy%20premise%20is%2C%20if%20you%20actually%20think%20that%20one%20person%20can%20do%20all%20of%20that%2C%20this%20isn't%20the%20place%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Olsen%20says.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20could%20ever%20succeed%20at%20having%2027%20priorities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScrolling%20through%20LinkedIn%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20find%20job%20descriptions%20that%20rival%20CVS%20receipts%2C%20with%20so%20many%20responsibilities%20they're%20split%20under%20several%20subheads.%20A%20corporate%20communications%20lead%20listing%20asks%20applicants%20to%20meet%20nine%20qualifications%2C%20bolstered%20by%20another%20six%20%26quot%3Bpreferred%20qualifications%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20cover%2022%20responsibilities.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyear-coding-changed-forever-silicon-valley-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20engineer%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%2011%20%26quot%3Bessential%20duties%20and%20responsibilities%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20another%2011%20skills%20(including%20a%20%26quot%3Bpositive%20energetic%20attitude%26quot%3B).%20A%20lead%20of%20revenue%20strategy%20and%20operations%20is%20expected%20to%20perform%2013%20responsibilities%20and%20meet%20a%20dozen%20qualifications%20split%20into%20five%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20length%20of%20a%20job%20title%20has%20jumped%20from%202.4%20words%20in%202013%20to%20four%20words%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20job%20listings%20from%20HR%20software%20company%20BambooHR%2C%20which%20found%20that%20lengthy%2C%20highly%20specific%2C%20niche%20roles%20were%20driving%20up%20the%20character%20count.%20Hiring%20platform%20Greenhouse%20found%20that%20the%20average%20job%20description%20character%20count%20has%20increased%207.4%25%20from%202022%20to%202026%20%E2%80%94%20the%20four%20years%20since%20ChatGPT%20became%20widely%20available.%20Over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20number%20of%20sections%20in%20a%20job%20listing%20grew%20by%20nearly%2014%25%20and%20skills%20sections%20jumped%20by%20almost%2016%25.%20Indeed%20found%20that%20the%20number%20of%20words%20in%20a%20post%20grew%2014.3%25%20from%202021%20to%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20puffing%20up%20the%20ever-expanding%20job%20description%3F%20What%20else%3A%20AI.%20In%20some%2C%20hiring%20managers%20have%20layered%20new%20AI%20proficiency%20and%20pedagogy%20expectations%20on%20top%20of%20standard%20job%20tasks.%20Other%20listings%2C%20recruiters%20tell%20me%2C%20have%20inflated%20because%20hiring%20managers%20generated%20them%20with%20long-winded%20LLMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManagers%20don't%20have%20to%20edit%20themselves%2C%20so%20they're%20just%20dumping%20the%20kitchen%20sink%20in%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Marc%20Cenedella%2C%20CEO%20of%20career%20site%20Ladders%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20dumping%20in%20nice-to-haves%2C%20could-haves%2C%20and%20passing%20thoughts%20they%20had%20in%20the%20shower%20this%20morning.%26quot%3B%20The%20descriptions%20balloon%20with%20input%20from%20people%20without%20direct%20oversight%20over%20the%20role%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20benefits%20to%20applicants%20or%20recruiters%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-taking-pay-cuts-huge-numbers-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20hunt%20is%20broken%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Recruiters%20say%20cover%20letters%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-managers-arent-reading-resumes-slop-2026-3%3Fmrfhud%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20lost%20their%20meaning%20at%20a%20time%20when%20anyone%20can%20customize%20their%20applications%20to%20roles%20by%20running%20them%20through%20ChatGPT.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20job%20descriptions%2C%20AI%20compounds%20the%20problem%3A%20Its%20verbosity%20leads%20to%20long%20bulleted%20lists%20centered%20on%20corporate%20jargon-slop%20buzzwords%2C%20but%20the%20technology%20has%20also%20shifted%20expectations%20rapidly.%20Workers%20are%20encouraged%2C%20and%20even%20expected%2C%20to%20take%20on%20more%20with%20AI%20at%20their%20disposal.%20Those%20looking%20for%20work%20must%20sort%20through%20walls%20of%20text%20to%20discern%20whether%20they're%20qualified%2C%20adding%20another%20barrier%20to%20the%20convoluted%2C%20lengthy%20job%20hunt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20paragraphs%20doesn't%20make%20for%20a%20better%20hire%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Cenedella.%20%26quot%3BMore%20bullet%20points%20doesn't%20make%20for%20a%20more%20on%20target%20fit.%20And%20so%20these%20longer%20and%20longer%20job%20descriptions%20are%20hurting%20candidates%20and%20they're%20hurting%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20signal%20to%20the%20best%20person%20for%20the%20job%20might%20be%20a%20concise%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20earliest%20known%20job%20ad%20dates%20back%20to%201752%2C%20placed%20in%20a%20Virginia%20newspaper%20by%20an%20employer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Flifestyle%2Fworkplace%2Fjob-listings-advertisements-history-7bb61fe0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseeking%20an%20oysterman%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20were%20only%20two%20qualifications%2C%20that%20the%20applicant%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20sober%20person%2C%20well%20recommended.%26quot%3B%20For%20more%20than%20200%20years%2C%20the%20ads%20stayed%20fairly%20succinct%2C%20as%20employers%20paid%20by%20line%20to%20list%20them%20in%20newspapers.%20Then%20online%20job%20boards%20freed%20them%20from%20the%20confines%20of%20the%20classifieds.%20Tedious%20applicant%20tracking%20systems%20and%20additional%20application%20questions%20or%20exams%20have%20lengthened%20the%20process.%20The%20jump%20picked%20up%20before%20generative%20AI%20became%20widely%20available%2C%20and%20BambooHR%20data%20shows%20that%20job%20descriptions%20increased%2017%25%20in%20character%20length%20from%202016%20to%202025%2C%20with%20the%20biggest%20acceleration%20coming%20between%202021%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20gotten%20so%20far%20away%20from%20what%20the%20actual%20intent%20of%20a%20job%20description%20is%20and%20what%20it%20should%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Trent%20Cotton%2C%20head%20of%20talent%20insights%20at%20recruiting%20software%20company%20ICIMS.%20Companies%20started%20adding%20lines%20about%20company%20culture%20and%20seeking%20to%20%26quot%3Bsell%20the%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Cotton%20says%2C%20but%20that%20kind%20of%20culture%20fit%20talk%20better%20suits%20a%20job%20interview.%20The%20listing%2C%20he%20says%2C%20should%20act%20like%20a%20scorecard%2C%20where%20the%20candidate%2C%20recruiter%2C%20and%20hiring%20manager%20can%20evaluate%20a%20person's%20skills%20and%20compatibility%20to%20the%20job.%20%26quot%3BHiring%20managers%20and%20recruiters%20are%20trying%20to%20make%20it%20so%20verbose%20to%20try%20and%20create%20some%20type%20of%20way%20to%20siphon%20out%20candidates%2C%20but%20they're%20going%20about%20it%20the%20wrong%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20just%20adding%20a%20lot%20of%20paragraphs%20but%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20substance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20now%20prioritize%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-accelerating-trend-job-hires-college-degrees-matter-less-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskills-based%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weighing%20practical%20abilities%20over%20prestigious%20degrees%20and%20experience%20at%20top-tier%20companies.%20This%20shift%20has%20also%20led%20the%20skills%20sections%20of%20job%20listings%20to%20swell.%20%26quot%3BTo%20match%20a%20job%20to%20talent%20or%20talent%20to%20a%20job%2C%20they're%20putting%20as%20much%20information%20into%20that%20job%20post%20as%20possible%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20AI%20match%20the%20skills%20listed%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20those%20in%20a%20job%20post%2C%20Tara%20Marcelle%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20recruiting%20for%20staffing%20firm%20Manpower's%20US%20operations%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20really%20help%20to%20rank%20those%20candidates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20rambling%20job%20descriptions%20reflect%20the%20major%20upheaval%20coming%20for%20white%20collar%20work.%20Marketers%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeginners-guide-ai-vibe-coding-lovable-base44-claude-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibe%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20software%20engineers%20review%20more%20code%2C%20and%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-says-ai-letting-one-employee-do-work-of-teams-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20promoted%20a%20future%20where%20one%20person%20may%20do%20the%20work%20once%20handled%20by%20a%20whole%20team%2C%20as%20some%20people%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-workplace-more-productive-less-social-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrangling%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20unknown%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Michelle%20Volberg%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20recruiting%20company%20Twill.%20The%20posts%20are%20padded%2C%20and%20become%20%26quot%3Blike%20an%20umbrella%2C%20where%20they're%20just%20putting%20in%20all%20the%20possible%20scenarios%20that%20this%20person%20will%20do%20within%20the%20next%20six%20to%20nine%20months%2C%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20who%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20six%20months%20from%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20burgeoning%20job%20description%20isn't%20just%20a%20nuisance.%20Women%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20apply%20for%20jobs%20if%20they%20don't%20meet%20every%20stated%20qualification%2C%20and%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20apply%20for%20jobs%20with%20vague%20language%20in%20the%20listing%2C%20because%20they%20fear%20they%20will%20be%20underqualified%20for%20a%20job.%20Men%20worry%20less%20about%20having%20an%20exact%20skills%20match%20before%20clicking%20to%20apply%2C%20research%20from%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20shows.%20This%20imposter%20syndrome%20can%20perpetuate%20low%20numbers%20of%20women%20in%20leadership%20positions%20and%20in%20male-dominated%20fields.%20A%20job%20listing%20in%20search%20of%20a%20unicorn%20could%20spook%20qualified%20applicants%20from%20applying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApplicants%20have%20AI%20in%20their%20arsenal%2C%20too.%20They%20ask%20large%20language%20models%20to%20customize%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20cover%20letters%20to%20include%20the%20buzzwords%20and%20skills%2C%20and%20recruiters%20then%20have%20to%20suss%20out%20who%20can%20really%20do%20the%20job.%20Getting%20a%20set%20of%20applicants%20who%20bring%20an%20authentic%2C%20AI-free%20application%20to%20the%20table%20might%20require%20standing%20out%20amidst%20the%20corporate%20AI%20slop%20in%20other%20job%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJamie%20Hodari%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20coworking%20space%20Industrious%2C%20is%20looking%20for%20someone%20to%20take%20his%20CEO%20job.%20The%20description%20he%20wrote%20isn't%20brief%2C%20but%20it%20swaps%20typical%20corporate%20speak%20for%20a%20list%20of%20cheeky%20list%20of%20the%20people%20the%20CEO%20will%20manage%2C%20from%20members%20of%20a%20book%20club%20to%20two%20people%20duking%20it%20out%20over%20control%20of%20the%20thermostat%2C%20and%20ends%20with%20how%20the%20job%20will%20come%20with%20decision%20making%20about%20managing%20people%20who%20may%20experience%20difficult%20personal%20situations%20(%26quot%3Bthe%20truest%20description%20of%20this%20job%20isn't%20a%20list%20of%20responsibilities%2C%20it's%20a%20list%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads).%20Hodari%20tells%20me%20he%20thought%20of%20the%20description%20as%20a%20note%20to%20his%20successor%2C%20the%20way%20an%20outgoing%20president%20leaves%20one%20to%20the%20incoming%20president-elect.%20He%20also%20says%20that%20authentic%2C%20less-scripted%20approach%20became%20the%20%26quot%3Bsingle%20most%20effective%20recruiting-related%20thing%20I've%20ever%20done%20in%20my%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20applicants%20have%20met%20the%20message%20with%20their%20own%20deeply%20personalized%20applications%20and%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20job%20market%20where%20AI%20writes%20the%20job%20descriptions%2C%20edits%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20evaluates%20them%2C%20recruiters%20and%20applicants%20are%20growing%20frustrated%2C%20as%20it%20seems%20employers%20hold%20the%20power%20in%20the%20job%20market.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20it%20returns%20to%20a%20demanding%20market%20and%20you're%20competing%20for%20talent%2C%20all%20these%20things%20get%20fixed%2C%26quot%3B%20Cenedella%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20applicants%20are%20encouraged%20to%20keep%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20cover%20letters%20to%20a%20page%20each%2C%20those%20penning%20job%20ads%20may%20want%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-descriptions-longer-than-cvs-receipts-ai-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783239421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46950ae3bd3a50082bfa34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-descriptions-longer-than-cvs-receipts-ai-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20has%20made%20job%20descriptions%20expand%20into%20never-ending%2C%20confusing%20lists%20of%20required%20and%20nice-to-have%20skills%20and%20qualifications.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20visited%20the%20'world's%20first'%20AI%20art%20museum.%20It%20was%20dazzling%2C%20strange%2C%20and%20more%20thought-provoking%20than%20I%20expected.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20room%20covered%20in%20screens%20showing%20multi-colored%2C%20abstract%20AI-art.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442be1a25092c74cca1b77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDataland%2C%20now%20open%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20bills%20itself%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bworld's%20first%20museum%20of%20AI%20arts.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDataland%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world's%20first%20museum%20of%20AI%20arts%2C%26quot%3B%20opened%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20last%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20multi-sensory%20experience%20includes%20wearable%20devices%20and%20interactive%20AI-generated%20art.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20art%20is%20generated%20with%20an%20AI%20model%20that's%20trained%20on%20data%20from%20the%20natural%20world.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20descended%20an%20elevator%20into%20an%20expansive%20AI%20rainforest%2C%20where%20digital%20images%20of%20green%20and%20gold%2C%20vaguely%20resembling%20trees%2C%20flickered%20across%20every%20wall%2C%20while%20the%20floor%20and%20ceiling%20displayed%20an%20ever-evolving%20blue%2C%20root-like%20network%20that%20lit%20up%20in%20response%20to%20my%20steps.%20Sounds%20of%20an%20orchestra%20rang%20out%2C%20punctuated%20by%20the%20chirping%20of%20crickets.%20I%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20familiar%20scent%2C%20herby%20and%20spicy%2C%20like%20cutting%20into%20a%20fresh%20jalape%C3%B1o.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20entered%20Dataland%2C%20billed%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world's%20first%20museum%20of%20AI%20arts%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20opened%20last%20month%20in%20downtown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-do-in-los-angeles-california%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Angeles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20there%20to%20see%20the%20inaugural%20exhibit%2C%20%26quot%3BMachine%20Dreams%3A%20Rainforest%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20features%20five%20galleries%20of%20multi-sensory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-studio-ghibli-ai-art-image-generator-backlash-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eart%20generated%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20trained%20on%20data%20from%20the%20natural%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20stand%20inside%20an%20immersive%20room%20filled%20with%20colorful%20flower%20and%20nature%20imagery%20on%20the%20walls%20and%20ceiling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442d8ee218c3b62535f962%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDataland%20was%20founded%20by%20media%20artist%20Refik%20Anadol%20and%20his%20partner%2C%20artist%20Efsun%20Erkili%C3%A7.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%2C%20a%20collaborator%20on%20Dataland%2C%20says%20the%20museum%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Fcompany-news%2Foutreach-and-initiatives%2Farts-culture%2Fdataland-ai-art-museum%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Cloud%3C%2Fa%3E%20tools%20to%20create%20generative%20soundscapes%2C%20sense%20visitors'%20emotions%2C%20adjust%20scents%20%26quot%3Balgorithmically%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20respond%20to%20human%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20time%20when%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-use-gaining-in-hollywood-stigma-secret-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20in%20art%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20controversial%2C%20Dataland%20is%20the%20ultimate%20embrace%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20art%20was%20often%20beautiful%20and%20interactive%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Selfie%20of%20the%20author%20at%20the%20entrance%20to%20Dataland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442c46e218c3b62535f94f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDataland%20includes%20visuals%2C%20scents%2C%20sound%2C%20and%20interactive%20experiences.%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20weekday%20afternoon%20ticket%20was%20%2459%2C%20and%20after%20a%20group%20of%20about%2020%20of%20us%20formed%2C%20we%20were%20let%20into%20the%20first%20of%20five%20galleries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20screens%20of%20AI%20digital%20art.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442c76e218c3b62535f955%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20are%20standing%20inside%20a%20work%20of%20art%20that%20is%20still%20unfolding%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20recorded%20voice%20said.%20%26quot%3BYour%20presence%20shapes%20the%20world%20you're%20about%20to%20step%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20wristband%20and%20neck%20device.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442cae360acd489560dcb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVisitors%20to%20Dataland%20are%20given%20two%20wearable%20devices%20for%20the%20experience.%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20given%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwellness-tracking-apps-sleep-score-stress-hurting-health-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewearable%20devices%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20a%20wristband%20resembling%20a%20watch%20that%20tracked%20movement%2C%20temperature%2C%20and%20pulse%2C%20and%20a%20U-shaped%20device%20worn%20around%20the%20neck%20that%20emitted%20scents.%20Rather%20than%20fill%20the%20rooms%20with%20a%20single%20scent%2C%20each%20person%20would%20be%20exposed%20to%20different%20scents%20on%20their%20individual%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20wristband%20and%20screen%20in%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442d0ea25092c74cca1b7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20could%20see%20my%20movements%2C%20labeled%20M4%2C%20projected%20on%20a%20screen.%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20visuals%20were%20often%20trippy%2C%20ranging%20from%20abstract%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20wave%20of%20colorful%20balls%20that%20resembled%20Dippin'%20Dots%20%E2%80%94%20to%20more%20literal%2C%20like%20fantastical%20flower%20shapes%20or%20pink%20and%20blue%20birds%20fluttering%20across%20the%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22