360acd489560dcc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVisitors%20interacted%20with%20the%20space%2C%20watching%20their%20steps%20and%20waving%20their%20hands%20to%20see%20how%20the%20art%20responded.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20the%20screens%20went%20dark%2C%20and%20light%20circles%20appeared%20around%20each%20of%20our%20feet%2C%20displaying%20our%20pulse%20and%20temperature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20museum%2C%20the%20wristbands%20track%20your%20%26quot%3Bskin's%20electricity%26quot%3B%20in%20order%20to%20%26quot%3Bcapture%20your%20response%20to%20the%20artwork%20within.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse-workers-wearable-device-right-station-link-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracks%20your%20movements%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20the%20space%2C%20and%20on%20one%20screen%2C%20I%20could%20see%20myself%2C%20labeled%20M4%20per%20my%20assigned%20wristband%2C%20walking%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Feet%20stand%20on%20a%20blue%20digital%20projection%20showing%20a%20circular%20Temperature%20gauge.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a442e04e218c3b62535f96d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20screen%20showed%20how%20each%20person%20in%20the%20room%20reacted%20to%20the%20space%20%E2%80%94%20I%20could%20see%20the%20line%20for%20me%2C%20M4%2C%20on%20graphs%20that%20showed%20changes%20in%20my%20%26quot%3Bemotion%20temperature%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bheartbeat%26quot%3B%20during%20my%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20bit%20interesting%20to%20see%20my%20avatar%20on%20the%20screen%20and%20realize%20how%20long%20I'd%20spent%20in%20each%20room%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20enti