%20the%20films%20came%20out%20of%20the%20experience.%20I%20was%20in%20a%20long-running%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Marta%20Balaga%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Harry%20Styles%20sheds%20tears%20after%20breaking%20most%20performances%20record%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783238611000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-132192737%2Cimgsize-296439.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fharry-styles-sheds-tears-after-breaking-most-performances-record-of-wembley-stadium-thanks-fans-after-11th-night%2Farticleshow%2F132192733.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F132192733.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHarry%20Styles%20became%20visibly%20emotional%2C%20shedding%20tears%20after%20his%2011th%20performance%20at%20London's%20Wembley%20Stadium%20on%20July%203%2C%202026.%20This%20milestone%20marks%20a%20historic%20achievement%2C%20setting%20a%20new%20record%20for%20the%20most%20concerts%20by%20an%20artist%20in%20the%20venue%20within%20a%20single%20year.%20The%20singer's%20heartfelt%20reaction%20underscored%20the%20significance%20of%20this%20record-breaking%20run%2C%20supporting%20his%20latest%20album.%20Notably%2C%20he%20missed%20Taylor%20Swift's%20wedding%20due%20to%20his%20demanding%20schedule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NATO's%20eastern%20flank%20prepares%20to%20fend%20off%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20with%20or%20without%20America%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20guard%20patrols%20the%20newly%20built%20fence%20along%20the%20Russia-Finland%20border%20in%20Finland's%20North%20Karelia%20region.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42cc47a25092c74cca1117%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20guard%20patrols%20the%20newly%20built%20fence%20along%20the%20Russia-Finland%20border%20in%20Finland's%20North%20Karelia%20region.%3Cp%3EAlessandro%20RAMPAZZO%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENORTH%20KARELIA%2C%20Finland%20%E2%80%94%20Bears%2C%20wolves%20and%20moose%20still%20cross%20the%20frontier%20freely%2C%20but%20for%20the%20border%20guards%20patrolling%20this%20stretch%20of%20fields%20and%20forest%2C%20this%20is%20where%20NATO%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20line%20of%20wooden%20poles%20and%20painted%20markers%20cuts%20through%20the%20light%20green%20grass%2C%20separating%20Finland%20from%20Russia%20along%20the%20alliance's%20longest%20border%20with%20Moscow%20%E2%80%94%201%2C343%20kilometers%20(835%20miles)%20of%20increasingly%20militarized%20territory.%20The%20crossing%20has%20been%20closed%20since%202023%2C%20the%20year%20after%20the%20Kremlin's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20On%20the%20other%20side%20lies%20land%20Finland%20lost%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20when%20it%20was%20left%20to%20fight%20largely%20on%20its%20own%20in%20the%20early%20months%20of%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReporters%20from%20Axel%20Springer's%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20traveled%20to%20three%20exposed%20stretches%20of%20Europe's%20eastern%20frontier%20%E2%80%94%20Finland's%20forested%20border%20with%20Russia%2C%20Poland's%20fortified%20line%20with%20Kaliningrad%20and%20Belarus%20and%20Lithuania's%20vulnerable%20edge%20near%20the%20Suwa%C5%82ki%20Gap%20%E2%80%94%20to%20see%20how%20ready%20NATO's%20frontline%20states%20are%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20Moscow%20will%20attack%20the%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20observed%20was%20a%20continent%20racing%20to%20harden%20its%20eastern%20edge%20against%20a%20threat%20it%20can%20no%20longer%20assume%20Washington%20will%20handle.%20As%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20questions%20old%20security%20guarantees%20and%20looks%20to%20reduce%20America's%20military%20footprint%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20countries%20closest%20to%20Russia%20are%20building%20fortifications%2C%20expanding%20reserves%2C%20buying%20tanks%20and%20drones%20and%20preparing%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20first%20days%20of%20any%20conflict%20may%20be%20theirs%20to%20fight%20largely%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20his%20reelection%20in%202024%2C%20Trump%20has%20repeatedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fdonald-trump-nato-summit-sidesteps-article-5-mark-rutte-eu-defense-budget-russia-vladimir-putin-iran-israel-strikes-qatar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20into%20question%3C%2Fa%3E%20Washington's%20commitment%20to%20NATO's%20Article%205%2C%20the%20foundational%20clause%20under%20which%20an%20attack%20on%20one%20member%20is%20treated%20as%20an%20attack%20on%20all.%20The%20uncertainty%20only%20deepened%20after%20the%20war%20in%20Iran%2C%20when%20the%20president%20and%20his%20team%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fdonald-trump-anger-nato-allies-europe-united%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreatened%20to%20reassess%3C%2Fa%3E%20US%20membership%20in%20NATO%20in%20response%20to%20European%20allies'%20refusal%20to%20join%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmeduza.io%2Fen%2Ffeature%2F2026%2F06%2F10%2Fjoint-investigation-maps-russia-s-military-buildup-along-its-nato-border-finland-could-now-face-80-000-russian-troops%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esatellite%20imagery%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20Russia%20has%20built%20up%20its%20armed%20presence%20along%20its%20border%20with%20Finland%20and%20other%20EU%20countries%2C%20building%20barracks%20and%20staging%20military%20vehicles%20in%20what%20the%20head%20of%20Swedish%20military%20intelligence%20has%20described%20as%20preparation%20for%20a%20possible%20confrontation%20with%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20a%20superpower%2C%20and%20we're%20a%20small%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Col.%20Matti%20Pitk%C3%A4niitty%2C%20commander%20of%20Finland's%20North%20Karelia%20Border%20Guard%20District%2C%20while%20driving%20to%20the%20border.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20when%20you%20sleep%20next%20to%20a%20bear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinland%20never%20forgot%20the%20lessons%20of%20what%20it%20calls%20its%20Winter%20War%2C%20when%20it%20halted%20an%20unprovoked%20attack%20in%201939%20by%20the%20Soviet%20dictator%20Joseph%20Stalin%20but%20lost%20roughly%20a%20tenth%20of%20its%20territory.%20While%20much%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20Europe%20spent%20the%20decades%20after%20the%20Cold%20War%20cutting%20armies%20and%20cashing%20in%20the%20peace%20dividend%2C%20Helsinki%20kept%20conscription%2C%20maintained%20vast%20reserves%20and%20built%20its%20defenses%20around%20the%20assumption%20that%20Russia%20might%20one%20day%20come%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Winter%20War%2C%20Finland%20felt%20very%20alone%2C%20with%20very%20little%20help%20from%20other%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pitk%C3%A4niitty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20dozen%20Finnish%20defense%20officials%2C%20military%20officers%2C%20lawmakers%20and%20analysts%20interviewed%20for%20this%20article%20described%20their%20nation%20as%20unsurprised%20by%20Russia's%202022%20assault%20on%20Ukraine.%20And%20even%20after%20Finland%20joined%20NATO%20in%202023%2C%20Helsinki%20has%20continued%20to%20view%20the%20alliance%20as%20a%20reinforcement%20of%20its%20own%20defense%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20substitute%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20happy%20to%20be%20in%20an%20alliance%2C%20but%20we%20still%20understand%20that%20we%20will%20take%20the%20first%20blow%20alone%2C%20before%20NATO's%20Article%205%20is%20activated%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jukka%20Kopra%2C%20a%20Finnish%20lawmaker%20who%20chaired%20the%20parliament's%20defense%20committee%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20mutual%20defense%20clause%20that%20underpins%20the%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20trust%20the%20US%20as%20our%20ally%2C%20a%20member%20of%20NATO%2C%20but%20we%20realize%20they%20have%20crucial%20interests%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Kopra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5da167d-336f-45ac-999b-682c44a230ad%5C%22%3EFinland%3A%20'Total%20defense'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223936%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Chinook%20helicopter%20carrying%20British%20paratroopers%20took%20part%20in%20NATO%20exercises%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Finnish%20military%2C%20at%20a%20training%20ground%20less%20than%2030%20miles%20from%20the%20Russian%20border.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d0c8a25092c74cca114b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222624%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Chinook%20helicopter%20carrying%20British%20paratroopers%20took%20part%20in%20NATO%20exercises%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Finnish%20military%2C%20at%20a%20training%20ground%20less%20than%2030%20miles%20from%20the%20Russian%20border.%3Cp%3EPA%20Images%20via%20Reuters%20Connect%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20decades%2C%20Finland%20built%20its%20preparedness%20around%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Btotal%20defense%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mobilizable%20population%2C%20civil%20resilience%2C%20shelters%20and%20a%20military%20designed%20to%20keep%20fighting%20with%20or%20without%20allies.%20The%20country%20can%20mobilize%20nearly%20870%2C000%20reservists%20out%20of%20a%20population%20of%205.6%20million%2C%20a%20figure%20set%20to%20reach%20one%20million%20by%202031.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20fair%20to%20say%20Finland%20is%20more%20ready%20to%20fight%20alone%20than%20other%20frontline%20countries.%20The%20US%20wind-down%20doesn't%20impact%20its%20readiness%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eoin%20Miche%C3%A1l%20McNamara%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20fellow%20at%20the%20Finnish%20Institute%20of%20International%20Affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinland%20spends%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.treasuryfinland.fi%2Fannualreview2025%2Foperating-environment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%203%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20GDP%20on%20defense%20and%2C%20in%20line%20with%20its%20commitments%20to%20NATO%2C%20it%20intends%20to%20raise%20that%20figure%20to%205%20percent%20by%202035.%20Its%20air%20force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Filmavoimat.fi%2Fen%2F-%2Fenglanniksi%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Finnish%2520personnel%2520will%2520start%2CF%252D35%2520capability%2520into%2520service.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpects%20to%20receive%3C%2Fa%3E%20US-made%20F-35%20fighter%20jets%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%20Like%20most%20European%20militaries%2C%20the%20Finnish%20armed%20forces%20are%20still%20catching%20up%20on%20drone%20warfare%2C%20but%20on%20land%20they%20have%20one%20of%20Europe's%20largest%20artillery%20arsenals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStalin%20called%20artillery%20the%20god%20of%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNamara.%20%26quot%3BUnlike%20a%20lot%20of%20Western%20countries%2C%20Russia%20never%20forgot%20about%20artillery.%20Finns%20never%20forgot%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Finland's%20greatest%20military%20assets%20is%20the%20land%20itself.%20An%20army%20invading%20from%20the%20east%20would%20have%20to%20move%20through%20a%20country%20of%20few%20roads%2C%20dense%20forests%2C%20deep%20snow%20and%20freezing%20temperatures%2C%20with%20little%20light%20in%20winter%20and%20almost%20none%20of%20the%20darkness%20that%20conceals%20movement%20in%20summer.%20In%20the%20woods%2C%20long%2C%20slender%20gray-white%20trunks%20stand%20so%20close%20together%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20see%20more%20than%2050%20meters%20ahead.%20In%20spring%2C%20when%20the%20leaves%20turn%20bright%20green%2C%20visibility%20drops%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Finland's%20army%20relies%20on%20artillery%20like%20this%20155mm%20self-propelled%20howitzer.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d228a25092c74cca115b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224115%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinland's%20army%20relies%20on%20artillery%20like%20this%20155mm%20self-propelled%20howitzer.%3Cp%3ESTOYAN%20NENOV%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20without%20the%20US%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20Finland%20would%20have%20to%20fight%20entirely%20on%20its%20own.%20Several%20European%20countries%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20keeping%20Russia%20off%20NATO's%20northern%20flank%2C%20according%20to%20Charly%20Salonius-Pasternak%20of%20the%20Helsinki-based%20Nordic%20West%20Office%20think%20tank%2C%20referring%20specifically%20to%20Norway%2C%20Sweden%20and%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Finland%20would%20face%20a%20Russian%20army%20with%20more%20manpower%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20use%20sheer%20numbers%20in%20ways%20the%20alliance%20cannot%20easily%20match.%20%26quot%3BSince%20the%20Winter%20War%2C%20the%20very%20basics%20haven't%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pitk%C3%A4niitty%2C%20the%20border%20guard%20commander.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20use%20the%20terrain%2C%20operate%20the%20environment%20better%20than%20anyone%20else%20%E2%80%94%20then%2C%20we%20have%20leverage%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BIs%20the%20forest%20a%20typical%20Russian%20battle%20environment%3F%20I%20would%20say%20no.%20Their%20lessons%20are%20learned%20in%20more%20open%20environments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinland%20is%20now%20trying%20to%20teach%20its%20NATO%20allies%20how%20to%20fight%20on%20that%20ground.%20In%20May%2C%20two%20multinational%20exercises%20in%20southeastern%20Finland%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gouv.fr%2Fterre%2Factualites%2Fnorthern-star-renforcer-linterroperabilite-milieu-exigeant%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorthern%20Star%2026%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmaavoimat.fi%2Fen%2F-%2Fkarelian-sword-26-to-be-held-in-southeastern-finland-in-may-2026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKarelian%20Sword%2026%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20were%20designed%20in%20part%20to%20show%20troops%20from%20countries%20including%20France%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20how%20to%20operate%20in%20Northern%20Europe's%20forests%2C%20lakes%20and%20swamps.%20US%20soldiers%20from%20the%20Virginia%20National%20Guard%20also%20took%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarelian%20Sword%20%E2%80%94%20conducted%20in%20Finland's%20Vekaranj%C3%A4rvi%20region%20%E2%80%94%20involved%20some%2010%2C000%20soldiers%20in%20a%20simulated%20invasion%20of%20the%20country.%20One%20main%20takeaway%20from%20days%20of%20drilling%20in%20the%20woods%20was%20that%20armored%20vehicles%20and%20drones%20are%20ill-adapted%20for%20Finland's%20forests.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20very%20hard%20for%20commercial%20drones%20to%20find%20Finnish%20troops%20in%20the%20forest%20because%20of%20the%20leaves%2C%20unless%20you%20have%20a%20thermal%20camera%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Col.%20Ari%20M%C3%A4%C3%A4tt%C3%A4%2C%20the%20Karelian%20brigade's%20deputy%20commander%20who%20commanded%20the%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nordic%20country%20is%20also%20preparing%20to%20add%20another%20obstacle.%20Alongside%20Poland%20and%20the%20three%20Baltic%20states%2C%20Helsinki%20withdrew%20last%20year%20from%20the%20Ottawa%20Convention%20banning%20anti-personnel%20landmines%2C%20arguing%20that%20Russia%20never%20joined%20the%20treaty%20and%20is%20already%20using%20the%20weapons%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Finnish%20military%20officers%20confirmed%20to%20the%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20that%20the%20country's%20defense%20forces%20plan%20to%20purchase%20anti-personnel%20landmines%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%20The%20mines%20would%20not%20be%20deployed%20in%20peacetime%2C%20they%20said%2C%20but%20would%20be%20available%20if%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20Russian%20invasion%20became%20more%20imminent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20quite%20a%20long%20border%20with%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20First%20Lt.%20Terra%20Tevaj%C3%A4rvi%2C%20a%2033-year-old%20reservist%20and%20trained%20mechanized%20infantry%20officer%20who%20works%20as%20a%20filmmaker.%20Standing%20in%20a%20clearing%2C%20with%20the%20sounds%20of%20gunshots%20in%20the%20distance%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BLandmines%20would%20help%20slow%20%5Ban%20attacker%5D%20down%20and%20make%20our%20lives%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c8c2745-096d-49c2-8801-4723c579b648%5C%22%3ENuclear%20gap%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223296%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22France%20has%20proposed%20deploying%20jets%20like%20the%20Dassault%20Rafale%20fighter%2C%20which%20is%20capable%20of%20carrying%20a%20nuclear-armed%20cruise%20missile%2C%20to%20allied%20countries.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d515a25092c74cca1170%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFrance%20has%20proposed%20deploying%20jets%20like%20the%20Dassault%20Rafale%20fighter%2C%20which%20is%20capable%20of%20carrying%20a%20nuclear-armed%20cruise%20missile%2C%20to%20allied%20countries.%3Cp%3EStephane%20Mahe%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20domain%20where%20geography%2C%20conscription%20and%20military%20readiness%20offer%20little%20protection%3A%20nuclear%20weapons.%20While%20Finland%20has%20practiced%20for%20a%20conventional%20defense%20for%20decades%2C%20it%20is%20only%20since%20it%20joined%20NATO%20three%20years%20ago%20that%20it%20has%20had%20to%20incorporate%20nuclear%20deterrence%20into%20its%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20joining%20the%20alliance%2C%20Helsinki%20has%20participated%20in%20its%20Nuclear%20Planning%20Group%2C%20taken%20part%20in%20nuclear%20exercises%20and%20begun%20rewriting%20laws%20that%20still%20reflected%20its%20long%20history%20outside%20the%20alliance.%20In%20June%2C%20Finnish%20lawmakers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Ffinland-lifts-nuclear-weapons-ban-nato-security-shift%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifted%20restrictions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20transport%20and%20storage%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20on%20Finnish%20territory%2C%20a%20legacy%20of%20its%20non-nuclear%20posture%20before%20NATO%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanging%20that%20framework%20had%20proven%20more%20contentious%20than%20the%20discussion%20about%20joining%20NATO%20itself.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.is.fi%2Fpolitiikka%2Fart-2000012064646.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpposition%20parties%20resisted%3C%2Fa%3E%20lifting%20the%20restrictions%2C%20while%20officials%20and%20analysts%20argued%20that%20Finland%20could%20not%20be%20a%20full%20participant%20in%20NATO%20defense%20planning%20without%20understanding%20how%20nuclear%20deterrence%20works.%20%26quot%3BReadiness%20in%20that%20regard%20is%20being%20learned%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNamara.%20%26quot%3BYou%20hear%20the%20phrase%3A%20'Finland%20needs%20to%20upgrade%20its%20nuclear%20IQ%20as%20a%20society.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinland's%20nuclear%20debate%20highlighted%20an%20uncomfortable%20truth.%20While%20the%20country%20is%20better%20positioned%20than%20most%20frontline%20countries%20to%20defend%20its%20territory%20without%20American%20ground%20forces%2C%20it's%20no%20more%20able%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20Europe%20to%20replace%20Washington's%20nuclear%20umbrella.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20has%20not%20publicly%20questioned%20that%20guarantee%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20unpredictability%20has%20pushed%20Helsinki%20and%20other%20European%20capitals%20to%20examine%20whether%20Europe%20can%20build%20a%20stronger%20deterrent%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20meeting%20with%20France's%20top%20general%20in%20the%20Finnish%20capital%20in%20June%2C%20the%20country's%20Defense%20Minister%20Antti%20H%C3%A4kk%C3%A4nen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fanttihakkanen%2Fstatus%2F2061752838280134678%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacknowledged%20talks%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Paris%20about%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron's%20proposal%20to%20broaden%20his%20country's%20nuclear%20deterrent%20to%20include%20other%20European%20countries%3Cstrong%3E.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20French%20president%2C%20who%20officially%20proposed%20the%20idea%20in%20March%2C%20has%20left%20what%20he%20means%20by%20it%20purposefully%20ambiguous.%20Paris%20has%20floated%20joint%20exercises%20and%20temporary%20deployments%20of%20nuclear-capable%20French%20fighter%20jets%2C%20but%20not%20a%20formal%20European%20nuclear%20guarantee.%20For%20Finland%2C%20it%20is%20still%20unclear%20what%20participation%20in%20the%20scheme%20would%20mean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Helsinki%20is%20hoping%20that%20hosting%20troops%20from%20two%20nuclear-armed%20allies%20%E2%80%94%20France%20and%20the%20UK%20%E2%80%94%20will%20add%20another%20layer%20of%20deterrence%2C%20even%20if%20the%20force%20itself%20is%20conventional.%20Paris%20and%20London%20have%20expressed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.highnorthnews.com%2Fpolitics%2Fnato-forward-land-forces-hq-to-northern-finland%2F1104218%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20in%20participating%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20NATO%20battalion%20that%20will%20be%20based%20in%20Sweden%20but%20operate%20in%20northern%20Finland.%20Designed%20to%20strengthen%20the%20alliance's%20presence%20in%20the%20high%20north%2C%20the%20force%20will%20be%20led%20by%20Stockholm%2C%20another%20formerly%20neutral%20government%20that%20joined%20the%20military%20alliance%20after%20Moscow's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20be%20on%20high%20alert%2C%20with%20high%20readiness%20to%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Col.%20Daniel%20Rydberg%2C%20who%20leads%20Sweden's%20NATO%20mission%20in%20northern%20Finland.%20Along%20with%20Finnish%20border%20guards%2C%20NATO%20troops%20would%20be%20among%20the%20first%20responders%20if%20Russia%20decided%20to%20test%20Finland%2C%20he%20said%20in%20a%20phone%20interview%20the%20day%20before%20the%20force's%20inauguration%20in%20June.%20%26quot%3BThe%20message%20to%20Russia%20is%20deterrence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20what%20that%20would%20mean%20in%20the%20case%20of%20an%20attack%20by%20the%20Kremlin%20will%20depend%20on%20people%20like%20Nuutti%20Kurikka%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20conscript%20whose%20great-grandfather%20fought%20in%20the%20Winter%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeep%20in%20the%20Finnish%20forest%2C%20Kurikka%2C%20a%20platoon%20leader%2C%20stood%20in%20front%20of%20a%20tank.%20The%20lesson%20of%20that%20war%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20mentality%20that%20we%20can%20overcome%20very%20hard%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20officials%20in%20many%20European%20capitals%2C%20he%20is%20not%20anxious%20about%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20ambiguity%20regarding%20NATO.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20good%20that%20the%20relationship%20is%20a%20bit%20shaky%2C%20but%20Finland%20is%20prepared%20to%20defend%20itself%20alone%20if%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20it%20before%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb2c87c6-9fb2-4c44-96f9-dc97d2b609f5%5C%22%3EPoland%3A%20'Eastern%20Shield'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Polish%20Army%20tank%20fires%20during%20an%20exercise%20near%20the%20Suwalki%20Gap%20in%20June%202026.%20Poland%20depends%20on%20force%20size%20to%20deter%20neighboring%20Russia.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d6ae360acd489560d2cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Polish%20Army%20tank%20fires%20during%20an%20exercise%20near%20the%20Suwa%C5%82ki%20Gap%20in%20June%202026.%20Poland%20depends%20on%20force%20size%20to%20deter%20neighboring%20Russia.%3Cp%3EAndrzej%20Iwanczuk%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202024%2C%20Polish%20Prime%20Minister%20Donald%20Tusk%20visited%20the%20small%20village%20of%20D%C4%85br%C3%B3wka%2C%20near%20his%20country's%20border%20with%20the%20Russian%20exclave%20of%20Kaliningrad%2C%20to%20inspect%20the%20first%20stretch%20of%20a%20new%20fortification%20system%20known%20as%20the%20Eastern%20Shield.%20Standing%20before%20reinforced%20concrete%20anti-tank%20barriers%20known%20as%20hedgehogs%2C%20Tusk%20delivered%20a%20message%20aimed%20at%20both%20Poles%20and%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20to%20explain%20to%20anyone%20that%20this%20border%20must%20be%20guarded%20exceptionally%20carefully%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Polish%20television%20reported%20that%20the%20first%20section%20had%20been%20completed%20ahead%20of%20schedule.%20And%20yet%2C%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20later%2C%20with%20the%20project%20roughly%20halfway%20to%20its%202028%20deadline%2C%20the%20hedgehogs%20still%20stand%20behind%20D%C4%85br%C3%B3wka%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20a%20few%20hundred%20meters%20farther%20on%2C%20the%20visible%20fortifications%20end%20abruptly.%20A%20local%20resident%20said%20the%20activity%20around%20the%20border%20surged%20before%20Tusk's%20visit%2C%20then%20disappeared.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20the%20prime%20minister's%20visit%2C%20dozens%20of%20trucks%2C%20cranes%20and%20troops%20passed%20through%20here%20day%20after%20day%2C%20week%20after%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20resident%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20visit%2C%20complete%20silence.%20The%20operations%20simply%20stopped.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Finland's%20answer%20to%20uncertainty%20is%20national%20readiness%2C%20Poland's%20is%20concrete%20barriers%2C%20sensors%2C%20drones%20and%20one%20of%20Europe's%20fastest-growing%20armies.%20Since%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Warsaw%20has%20recast%20itself%20as%20NATO's%20frontline%20state%3A%20buying%20weapons%20at%20a%20pace%20few%20allies%20can%20match%2C%20expanding%20its%20army%2C%20and%20pouring%20billions%20into%20new%20defenses%20along%20its%20borders%20with%20Belarus%20and%20Kaliningrad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20unmistakable%20%E2%80%94%20to%20Moscow%2C%20to%20Washington%20and%20to%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20that%20Poland%20is%20preparing%20not%20for%20a%20distant%20theoretical%20threat%2C%20but%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20war%20could%20come%20sooner%20than%20many%20Western%20capitals%20assume.%20Yet%20along%20parts%20of%20the%20very%20frontier%20where%20that%20deterrent%20is%20supposed%20to%20take%20shape%2C%20the%20gap%20between%20Poland's%20military%20ambition%20and%20the%20physical%20reality%20on%20the%20ground%20remains%20visible%3A%20fortifications%20appear%2C%20then%20stop%3B%20materials%20sit%20in%20warehouses%3B%20and%20local%20residents%20say%20the%20building%20frenzy%20has%20given%20way%20to%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoland%20is%20the%20largest%20country%20on%20NATO's%20eastern%20flank%20and%20the%20alliance's%20biggest%20defense%20spender%20by%20share%20of%20GDP.%20Warsaw%20had%20already%20exceeded%20NATO's%202%25%20target%20before%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%3B%20this%20year%2C%20it%20is%20set%20to%20spend%204.8%25%20of%20GDP%20on%20defense%20even%20as%20its%20economy%20continues%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20Poland%20sent%20more%20than%20300%20tanks%20from%20its%20own%20stocks%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20then%20moved%20to%20replace%20and%20expand%20its%20arsenal%20with%20off-the-shelf%20tanks%2C%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20support%20vehicles%20and%20rocket%20artillery%20from%20the%20United%20States%20and%20South%20Korea.%20Its%20army%20is%20NATO's%20third%20largest%2C%20behind%20the%20US%20and%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Border%20guards%20patrol%20a%20section%20of%20Poland's%20border%20with%20Belarus%20during%20a%20high-profile%20visit%20in%20June.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4533911aaffe3020cb0d71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221427%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBorder%20guards%20patrol%20a%20section%20of%20Poland's%20border%20with%20Belarus%20during%20a%20high-profile%20visit%20in%20June.%3Cp%3EWojtek%20RADWANSKI%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sheer%20mass%20of%20the%20Polish%20military%2C%20combined%20with%20Warsaw's%20role%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20buyers%20of%20US%20weapons%2C%20has%20earned%20Warsaw%20a%20reputation%20in%20Washington%20as%20a%20model%20ally.%20Even%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20while%20berating%20other%20European%20countries%20over%20defense%2C%20has%20regularly%20praised%20Poland.%20The%20US%20keeps%20thousands%20of%20troops%20in%20Poland%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20on%20a%20rotational%20basis%2C%20an%20arrangement%20the%20Polish%20government%20is%20keen%20to%20keep%20as%20a%20deterrent%20to%20any%20Russian%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20importance%20to%20NATO%20is%20not%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20spending.%20Its%20size%20and%20location%20make%20it%20the%20alliance's%20central%20frontline%20state%20in%20any%20potential%20confrontation%20with%20the%20Kremlin.%20During%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20West%20Germany%20was%20NATO's%20conventional%20bulwark%20against%20the%20Warsaw%20Pact.%20Today%2C%20Poland%20plays%20a%20similar%20role%20on%20NATO's%20eastern%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20Germany%20has%20long%20focused%20on%20quality%2C%20Poland%20stands%20for%20mass%20and%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Carlo%20Masala%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20the%20German%20Federal%20Armed%20Forces%20in%20Munich%20and%20one%20of%20Germany's%20most%20renowned%20security%20experts.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20Warsaw%20does%20not%20rule%20out%20having%20to%20fight%20tomorrow.%20It%20is%20what%20is%20called%20'fight%20tonight.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETusk's%20Eastern%20Shield%20project%20is%20Warsaw's%20attempt%20to%20reinforce%20its%20defenses%20along%20its%20800-kilometer%20(500-mile)%20frontier%20with%20Belarus%2C%20a%20close%20ally%20of%20Moscow's%2C%20and%20Kaliningrad%2C%20the%20heavily%20militarized%20Russian%20territory%20wedged%20between%20Poland%2C%20Lithuania%20and%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%20Designed%20as%20a%20network%20of%20obstacles%20meant%20to%20slow%20an%20attack%2C%20channel%20Russian%20forces%20and%20buy%20time%20for%20NATO%20to%20respond%2C%20the%20system%20includes%20anti-tank%20and%20infantry%20trenches%2C%20concrete%20barriers%2C%20bunkers%2C%20drones%2C%20thermal%20cameras%2C%20mines%20and%20nearby%20military%20units%2C%20while%20also%20using%20natural%20obstacles%20such%20as%20swampy%20terrain.%20When%20completed%2C%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20cost%20about%20%E2%82%AC10%20billion%20(%2411%20billion)%20according%20to%20Poland's%20defense%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoland's%20military%20buildup%20is%20part%20of%20a%20large-scale%2C%20multi-billion-dollar%20new%20deterrence%20and%20defense%20system%20along%20NATO's%20eastern%20border.%20Known%20as%20the%20Eastern%20Flank%20Deterrence%20Line%2C%20it%20is%20planned%20to%20stretch%20from%20Finland%20to%20Romania.%20Brig.%20Gen.%20Thomas%20Lowin%2C%20deputy%20chief%20of%20staff%20for%20operations%20at%20NATO%20Land%20Command%20in%20Izmir%2C%20says%20the%20alliance%20will%20build%20up%20much%20larger%20stockpiles%20of%20weapons%2C%20ammunition%20and%20equipment%20in%20border%20states%2C%20while%20establishing%20an%20%26quot%3Bautomated%20zone%26quot%3B%20of%20sensors%20and%20robotized%20weapons%20to%20help%20halt%20Russian%20forces%20early%20in%20any%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECezary%20Tomczyk%2C%20Poland's%20deputy%20defense%20minister%20and%20the%20official%20overseeing%20the%20project%2C%20called%20his%20country's%20part%20of%20the%20effort%20the%20largest%20fortification%20effort%20in%20Europe%20since%20World%20War%20II.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20building%20a%20border%20that%20sees%20further%2C%20reacts%20faster%20and%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20the%20enemy%20to%20act%20at%20every%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRussia%20must%20know%20one%20thing%3A%20Every%20kilometer%20of%20potential%20aggression%20will%20cost%20more%20time%2C%20more%20equipment%20and%20more%20resources.%20The%20Eastern%20Shield%20is%20intended%20to%20raise%20the%20price%20of%20aggression%20to%20an%20unacceptable%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ceebf58-8816-4f8a-93ef-66b0390f4100%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20section%20of%20Poland's%20border%20with%20Russia%20is%20laid%20with%20anti-tank%20obstacles%2C%20seen%20here%20in%202024.%20But%20along%20a%20farm%20nearby%2C%20the%20only%20obvious%20protection%20is%20a%20simple%20concertina-wire%20fence.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4536352680585ce91a2fad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20section%20of%20Poland's%20border%20with%20Russia%20is%20laid%20with%20anti-tank%20obstacles%2C%20seen%20here%20in%202024.%20But%20along%20a%20farm%20nearby%2C%20the%20only%20obvious%20protection%20is%20a%20simple%20concertina-wire%20fence.%3Cp%3EMarek%20Antoni%20Iwanczuk%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20however%2C%20along%20parts%20of%20the%20border%2C%20the%20Eastern%20Shield%20is%20still%20more%20promise%20than%20reality.%20Polish%20officials%20are%20reluctant%20to%20discuss%20delays%2C%20and%20not%20every%20element%20of%20the%20system%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20visible.%20But%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20border%20are%20not%20visibly%20fortified.%20A%20military%20facility%20near%20D%C4%85br%C3%B3wka%20warehouses%20large%20numbers%20of%20hedgehog%20anti-tank%20barriers%2C%20but%20since%20Tusk's%20visit%20to%20the%20village%2C%20none%20have%20been%20placed%20along%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoland's%20defense%20ministry%20told%20the%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20that%20engineering%20troops%2C%20using%20pre-positioned%20material%20from%20warehouses%2C%20would%20be%20able%20to%20erect%20fortifications%20along%20the%20entire%20border%20within%20seven%20to%2014%20days.%20But%20a%20logistics%20expert%20who%20has%20held%20senior%20military%20positions%20said%20some%20elements%20cannot%20be%20moved%20into%20place%20so%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaying%20one%20kilometer%20of%20reinforced%20concrete%20hedgehogs%20takes%20anywhere%20from%20several%20weeks%20to%20several%20months%2C%20depending%20on%20terrain%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20logistics%20expert%2C%20who%20was%20granted%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20sensitive%20defense%20matters.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20the%20army%20three%20weeks%20to%20fortify%20a%20relatively%20short%20section.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20short%20distance%20from%20D%C4%85br%C3%B3wka%2C%20an%20agritourism%20farm%20named%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20End%20of%20the%20World%26quot%3B%20welcomes%20visitors%20looking%20for%20a%20rural%20retreat.%20At%20the%20Russian%20border%2C%20less%20than%20100%20meters%20away%2C%20the%20only%20obvious%20protection%20is%20a%20simple%20concertina-wire%20fence%20and%20a%20scattering%20of%20warning%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%2C%20Wioletta%20Bornejko%2C%20does%20not%20want%20the%20new%20fortifications%20to%20reach%20her%20meadow.%20%26quot%3BI%20hope%20they%20don't%20put%20up%20those%20concrete%20hedgehogs%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20barbed%20wire%20scares%20away%20tourists.%20A%20neighbor%20recently%20closed%20down%20a%20similar%20business.%26quot%3B%20Others%20in%20the%20area%20say%20the%20constant%20talk%20of%20war%20has%20already%20hurt%20local%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20quiet%20is%20deceptive.%20Travel%20east%20from%20D%C4%85br%C3%B3wka%20and%20you'll%20reach%20the%20so-called%20Suwa%C5%82ki%20Gap.%20Ben%20Hodges%2C%20a%20retired%20general%20who%20served%20as%20the%20commander%20of%20US%20Army%20Europe%2C%20has%20described%20this%20short%20stretch%20of%20Polish%20and%20Lithuanian%20territory%20separating%20Kaliningrad%20from%20Belarus%20as%20NATO's%20Achilles'%20heel.%20The%20fear%20is%20that%20a%20Russian%20attack%20could%20try%20to%20close%20the%20corridor%20from%20both%20sides%2C%20cutting%20Poland%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20NATO%20from%20the%20Baltic%20states%20to%20the%20north.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarther%20east%2C%20Poland's%20border%20with%20Belarus%20stretches%20some%20420%20kilometers%20(260%20miles).%20There%2C%20the%20limits%20of%20the%20current%20defenses%20are%20even%20more%20evident.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20any%20other%20fortifications%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20soldier%20from%20a%20brigade%20serving%20on%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20border%20is%20protected%20only%20by%20a%204-meter-high%20(13-feet-high)%20fence%20built%20in%202022.%20Erected%20to%20stop%20migrants%20from%20crossing%20into%20Poland%2C%20it%20would%20offer%20little%20protection%20against%20tanks.%20Poland's%20defense%20ministry%20told%20the%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20that%20it%20currently%20%26quot%3Bhas%20material%20resources%20that%20allow%20it%20to%20secure%20border%20sections%20with%20a%20total%20length%20of%20over%20140%20kilometres%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%20a%20third%20of%20the%20length%20of%20the%20frontier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d41bae9d-86d7-4442-b36c-3f12f669102e%5C%22%3EDrone%20wall%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20February%20exercise%20showcased%20counter-drone%20systems%20that%20are%20part%20of%20Poland's%20drive%20to%20build%20a%20drone%20wall.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d91de218c3b62535ef75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20February%20exercise%20showcased%20counter-drone%20systems%20that%20are%20part%20of%20Poland's%20drive%20to%20build%20a%20so-called%20drone%20wall.%3Cp%3ESTR%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETanks%20and%20other%20traditional%20forces%20aren't%20the%20only%20thing%20Poland%20would%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20in%20case%20of%20a%20Russian%20attack.%20Anti-tank%20measures%20are%20of%20limited%20use%20when%20the%20weapons%20of%20choice%20fly%20far%20overhead%20and%20are%20cheap%20enough%20to%20exhaust%20conventional%20air%20defenses.%20And%20so%20the%20country%20is%20busy%20developing%20an%20anti-drone%20system%20it%20calls%20SAN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20development%20gained%20urgency%20after%2019%20Russian%20drones%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Frussia-drone-nato-incursions-poland-gaps-western-arsenal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eentered%20Polish%20airspace%20%3C%2Fa%3Elast%20year%2C%20forcing%20NATO%20aircraft%20to%20shoot%20them%20down%20with%20missiles%20from%20F-16%20and%20F-35%20jets%20%E2%80%94%20a%20response%20that%20cost%20millions%20of%20euros%20against%20drones%20worth%20a%20fraction%20of%20that.%20SAN%20is%20meant%20to%20allow%20Poland%20to%20defend%20against%20drones%20without%20relying%20on%20fighter%20jets.%20The%20system%2C%20sometimes%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrone%20wall%2C%26quot%3B%20could%20cost%20up%20to%20%E2%82%AC4%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20accounting%20for%20about%2040%25%20of%20the%20entire%20Eastern%20Shield.%20%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20watching%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tomczyk%2C%20Poland's%20deputy%20defense%20minister.%20%26quot%3BSo%20are%20we.%20We%20draw%20our%20conclusions%20faster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETomczyk%20said%20SAN%20would%20be%20Europe's%20largest%20and%20most%20advanced%20anti-drone%20effort.%20Within%2024%20months%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20Polish%20army%20is%20expected%20to%20receive%2018%20battery%20modules%2C%20including%20about%20700%20combat%20vehicles%2C%20radars%2C%20sensors%20and%20effectors%2C%20and%20roughly%20350%20systems%20to%20detect%20and%20counter%20aerial%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20a%20single%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20entire%20architecture%20for%20drone%20defense.%26quot%3B%20Construction%20of%20SAN%20began%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20and%20is%20scheduled%20for%20completion%20by%20the%20end%20of%202027%2C%20after%20which%20it%20will%20be%20permanently%20deployed%20on%20Poland's%20eastern%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Masala%2C%20the%20security%20expert%2C%20the%20drone%20wall%20and%20the%20Eastern%20Shield%20are%20part%20of%20the%20same%20strategy%3A%20to%20slow%20a%20Russian%20attack%20long%20enough%20for%20NATO%20to%20react.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20USA%20is%20withdrawing%20from%20Europe%20and%20that%20the%20Europeans%20currently%20lack%20deep-strike%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20have%20to%20ask%20ourselves%20which%20strategies%20make%20sense%20in%20the%20event%20of%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20is%20to%20aim%20at%20delaying%20the%20Russians.%20This%20is%20possible%20with%20the%20installations%20that%20Poland%20is%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20lesson%20from%20Ukraine%20is%20that%20not%20everything%20always%20has%20to%20be%20at%20150%20percent%2C%20but%20that%2080%25%20is%20sometimes%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c035adf-5bfc-4563-9d87-2f9d69bb98a6%5C%22%3ELithuania%3A%20'The%20Baltic%20Defense%20Line'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22German%20soldiers%20cross%20a%20path%20lined%20with%20anti-tank%20dragon's%20teeth%20during%20a%20June%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4538b71aaffe3020cb0fd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGerman%20soldiers%20cross%20a%20path%20lined%20with%20anti-tank%20dragon's%20teeth%20during%20a%20June%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania.%3Cp%3EKay%20Nietfeld%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20office%20of%20Raimundas%20Vaik%C5%A1noras%2C%20Lithuania's%20chief%20of%20defense%2C%20a%20map%20of%20the%20country%20lies%20spread%20across%20a%20table.%20Marked%20on%20it%20are%20the%20positions%20of%20German%20and%20American%20troops%20near%20the%20Belarusian%20border%20%E2%80%94%20a%20reminder%20that%2C%20for%20Lithuania%20and%20its%20Baltic%20neighbors%2C%20national%20defense%20depends%20on%20allies%20being%20close%20enough%20to%20quickly%20join%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVaik%C5%A1noras%2C%20who%20has%20led%20Lithuania's%20armed%20forces%20since%202024%2C%20does%20not%20think%20a%20Russian%20surprise%20attack%20is%20likely.%20NATO%20warning%20systems%2C%20he%20said%2C%20make%20large%20troop%20movements%20difficult%20to%20hide.%20Lithuania%20watches%20rail%20hubs%2C%20logistics%20sites%20and%20when%20Russia%20and%20Belarus%20hold%20military%20exercises%20across%20the%20border%2C%20its%20armed%20forces%20respond%20in%20kind.%20%26quot%3BWe%20organize%20exercises%20with%20equally%20strong%20or%20even%20stronger%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20Vaik%C5%A1noras%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20mirror%20the%20movements%20of%20the%20other%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lithuania's%20chief%20of%20defense%2C%20Raimundas%20Vaik%C5%A1noras%2C%20said%20his%20country%20matches%20or%20exceeds%20the%20scale%20of%20Russian%20military%20exercises%20held%20nearby%20as%20a%20deterrent.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45379c2680585ce91a2fca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELithuania's%20chief%20of%20defense%2C%20Raimundas%20Vaik%C5%A1noras%2C%20said%20his%20country%20matches%20or%20exceeds%20the%20scale%20of%20Russian%20military%20exercises%20held%20nearby%20as%20a%20deterrent.%3Cp%3ECarsten%20Hoffmann%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Finland%20is%20preparing%20to%20fight%20alone%20if%20it%20has%20to%20and%20Poland%20is%20building%20an%20army%20capable%20of%20doing%20the%20same%2C%20the%20Baltic%20countries%20do%20not%20have%20that%20luxury.%20Lithuania%2C%20Latvia%20and%20Estonia%20are%20too%20small%2C%20too%20exposed%20and%20too%20close%20to%20Russia%20and%20Belarus%20to%20trade%20territory%20for%20time.%20Connected%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20NATO%20by%20the%20roughly%2065-kilometer-wide%20(40-mile-wide)%20Suwa%C5%82ki%20Gap%2C%20they%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20being%20cut%20off%20by%20a%20lightning%20assault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20defense%20rests%20on%20a%20narrower%20calculation%3A%20make%20sure%20that%20NATO%20comes%20to%20their%20rescue.%20That%20makes%20them%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20unpredictability.%20And%20so%20the%20Baltic%20states%20have%20set%20out%20to%20bind%20their%20security%20as%20tightly%20as%20possible%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20continent%20%E2%80%94%20through%20border%20fortifications%2C%20pre-positioned%20obstacles%2C%20allied%20troops%20on%20their%20soil%20and%2C%20above%20all%2C%20a%20German%20brigade%20meant%20to%20ensure%20that%20any%20Russian%20attack%20would%20immediately%20become%20a%20European%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20conflict%20in%20the%20region%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20would%20enjoy%20a%20clear%20advantage.%20Russian%20troops%20would%20be%20fighting%20virtually%20on%20their%20own%20doorstep%2C%20while%20NATO%20reinforcements%20would%20have%20to%20move%20across%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20across%20the%20Atlantic%20%E2%80%94%20before%20reaching%20the%20front.%20Kaliningrad%20compounds%20the%20problem.%20One%20of%20Europe's%20most%20militarized%20areas%2C%20the%20Russian%20territory%20is%20packed%20with%20air-defense%20systems%2C%20missiles%20and%20surveillance%20technology.%20In%20wartime%2C%20Russian%20military%20units%20based%20there%20could%20threaten%20NATO%20supply%20routes%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20and%20along%20the%20Polish-Lithuanian%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELithuania's%20vulnerability%20is%20on%20display%20near%20the%20village%20of%20Lavori%C5%A1k%C4%97s%2C%20where%20a%20red%20sign%20warns%20Lithuanian%20citizens%20not%20to%20travel%20across%20the%20frontier%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20not%20risk%20your%20safety%20%E2%80%94%20do%20not%20travel%20to%20Belarus.%20You%20may%20fail%20to%20come%20back.%26quot%3B%20The%20government%20closed%20the%20crossing%20in%20early%202024%20on%20national%20security%20grounds.%20The%20border%20is%20lined%20with%20dense%20coils%20of%20razor%20wire%2C%20and%20rows%20of%20triangular%20concrete%20blocks%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20dragon's%20teeth%20%E2%80%94%20stand%20ready%20to%20stop%20enemy%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fortifications%20are%20part%20of%20the%20Baltic%20Defense%20Line%2C%20a%20joint%20defense%20project%20by%20Estonia%2C%20Latvia%20and%20Lithuania.%20Along%20NATO's%20eastern%20frontier%2C%20the%20three%20countries%20are%20preparing%20anti-tank%20ditches%2C%20bunkers%2C%20defensive%20obstacles%20and%20%E2%80%94%20more%20controversially%20%E2%80%94%20minefields.%20Like%20Finland%2C%20the%20Baltic%20countries%20have%20moved%20to%20leave%20the%20Ottawa%20Convention%2C%20which%20prohibits%20such%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20obstacles%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20an%20attacker%20to%20simply%20roll%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ralph%20Thiele%2C%20a%20retired%20colonel%20and%20chairman%20of%20the%20Political-Military%20Society%20in%20Berlin.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20stop%2C%20bring%20in%20combat%20engineers%20and%20clear%20a%20path.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Russian%20forces%20break%20through%2C%20they%20would%20have%20%26quot%3Bopen%20terrain%2C%26quot%3B%20Thiele%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eff70706-62ce-41f4-ad26-a7592e6227a7%5C%22%3EForward%20defense%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20soldiers%20trained%20with%20allies%20at%20Lithuania's%20Pabrad%C4%97%20Training%20Area%20in%20May.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42dd92360acd489560d2fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20trained%20with%20allies%20at%20Lithuania's%20Pabrad%C4%97%20Training%20Area%20in%20May.%3Cp%3ESgt.%20Nicodemus%20Taylor%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVaik%C5%A1noras%2C%20Lithuania's%20chief%20of%20defense%2C%20does%20not%20pretend%20his%20country%20can%20defend%20itself%20alone.%20The%20border%20fortifications%20are%20intended%20to%20slow%20Russians%20down%2C%20channel%20enemy%20forces%20onto%20predictable%20axes%20of%20advance%20and%20buy%20time%20for%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20of%20the%20Baltics%20relies%20on%20how%20long%20they%20can%20hold%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20how%20quickly%20NATO%20can%20reinforce%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20about%203%2C000%20soldiers%20from%20other%20NATO%20countries%20in%20Lithuania%2C%20he%20said%20in%20February%2C%20including%20German%2C%20Norwegian%2C%20Dutch%20and%20American%20troops.%20Since%20then%2C%20however%2C%20the%20rotational%20deployment%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20US%20soldiers%20has%20ended.%20Unlike%20previous%20rotations%2C%20no%20follow-on%20force%20has%20yet%20arrived%2C%20as%20Washington%20reviews%20its%20military%20posture%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20again%2C%20underscores%20the%20role%20European%20allies%20are%20playing%20on%20NATO's%20eastern%20flank.%20The%20most%20important%20addition%20is%20the%20German%20brigade%2C%20due%20to%20be%20permanently%20stationed%20in%20Lithuania%20by%20the%20end%20of%202027%2C%20when%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20consist%20of%20around%205%2C000%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20NATO's%20presence%20in%20the%20Baltic%20states%20was%20largely%20based%20on%20so-called%20tripwire%20forces%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20multinational%20units%20whose%20purpose%20was%20to%20ensure%20that%20any%20attack%20on%20the%20region%20would%20automatically%20draw%20the%20entire%20Alliance%20into%20the%20conflict.%20Today%2C%20NATO%20relies%20on%20forward%20defence.%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20defend%20every%20inch%20of%20Alliance%20territory%20from%20the%20outset.%20Still%2C%20the%20strategy%20continues%20to%20rely%20on%20reinforcements.%20It%20is%20unlikely%20that%20the%20troops%20stationed%20in%20Lithuania%20at%20present%20will%20be%20able%20to%20fight%20on%20their%20own%20indefinitely.%20How%20long%20they%20could%20hold%20out%20depends%20on%20how%20quickly%20additional%20NATO%20troops%20arrive%2C%20as%20well%20as%20on%20the%20scale%20and%20nature%20of%20a%20possible%20Russian%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20presence%20is%20important%20because%20the%20old%20NATO%20assumption%20%E2%80%94%20that%20the%20US%20would%20automatically%20lead%20any%20response%20to%20a%20Russian%20attack%20%E2%80%94%20is%20no%20longer%20one%20Europe%20can%20take%20for%20granted.%20%26quot%3BI%20very%20clearly%20feel%20that%20we%20have%20strong%20allies%20by%20our%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20Vaik%C5%A1noras%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20Germany%20has%20assumed%20a%20leadership%20role%20in%20NATO%20here%20is%20an%20important%20signal%2C%20including%20to%20our%20own%20population.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22German%20Army%20troops%20moved%20through%20smoke%20during%20the%20Freedom%20Shield%202026%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42e10ba25092c74cca11cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGerman%20Army%20troops%20moved%20through%20smoke%20during%20the%20Freedom%20Shield%202026%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania.%3Cp%3EKay%20Nietfeld%2FKay%20Nietfeld%2Fdpa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20such%20a%20leadership%20role%20could%20mean%20in%20practice%20was%20revealed%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2026%2F02%2F13%2Frussia-nato-wargame-germany-simulation-00778818%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutcome%20of%20a%20wargame%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20late%20last%20year%20by%20WELT%2C%20part%20of%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%2C%20together%20with%20the%20German%20Wargaming%20Center%20at%20the%20Bundeswehr%20University%20in%20Hamburg.%20The%20exercise%20tested%20how%20Germany%20would%20respond%20if%20Russia%20used%20a%20post-Ukraine%20ceasefire%20to%20threaten%20Lithuania%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20Washington%20declined%20to%20play%20its%20traditional%20role%20as%20NATO's%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20day%2C%20former%20senior%20politicians%2C%20military%20officers%2C%20intelligence%20officials%20and%20security%20experts%20took%20on%20the%20roles%20of%20the%20German%20government%2C%20its%20allies%20and%20the%20Kremlin.%20The%20scenario%20began%20with%20Russian%20troops%20remaining%20in%20Belarus%20after%20an%20exercise%20instead%20of%20withdrawing%20as%20announced%2C%20then%20concentrating%20near%20Lithuania's%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20was%20sobering.%20While%20Team%20Russia%20moved%20quickly%20toward%20a%20limited%20invasion%2C%20the%20German%20side%20held%20crisis%20meetings%20and%20focused%20on%20recruiting%20allies%20and%20building%20political%20support%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20preventing%20Moscow%20from%20achieving%20its%20military%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b32bbbf-9057-44fc-a5ca-db1dae8ca083%5C%22%3EThe%20new%20NATO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brig.%20Gen.%20Christoph%20Huber%20of%20the%20German%20Army%20emerges%20from%20a%20Puma%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%20during%20the%20Freedom%20Shield%202026%20exercises%20in%20Lithuania%20in%20June.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42dffbe218c3b62535ef9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrig.%20Gen.%20Christoph%20Huber%20of%20the%20German%20Army%20emerges%20from%20a%20Puma%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%20during%20the%20Freedom%20Shield%202026%20exercises%20in%20Lithuania%20in%20June.%20Germany%20plans%20to%20station%20a%20brigade%20in%20Lithuania%20by%202027.%3Cp%3EKay%20Nietfeld%2FKay%20Nietfeld%2Fdpa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20old%20NATO%2C%20German%20hesitation%20would%20have%20mattered%20less.%20The%20US%20would%20have%20been%20expected%20to%20take%20command%20politically%20and%20militarily%2C%20moving%20troops%2C%20aircraft%20and%20ships%20while%20European%20governments%20aligned%20behind%20it.%20But%20as%20the%20US%20reduces%20its%20role%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20defense%20of%20the%20eastern%20flank%20increasingly%20depends%20on%20a%20question%20the%20alliance%20has%20not%20yet%20fully%20answered%3A%20Is%20Europe%20ready%20to%20fight%20on%20its%20own%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHodges%2C%20the%20former%20US%20Army%20Europe%20commander%2C%20has%20warned%20that%2C%20in%20a%20worst%20case%20%E2%80%94%20if%20NATO%20is%20caught%20by%20surprise%20and%20Polish%20troops%20are%20unable%20to%20provide%20support%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Baltic%20countries%20could%20have%20to%20fight%20for%20up%20to%20two%20weeks%20without%20additional%20reinforcements%20from%20more%20distant%20allies.%20That%20is%20the%20window%20of%20time%20in%20which%20their%20allies%20would%20have%20to%20react.%20German%20and%20Lithuanian%20officials%20reject%20the%20notion%20that%20such%20a%20scenario%20would%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20A%20Russian%20attack%2C%20they%20say%2C%20would%20be%20preceded%20by%20visible%20military%20preparations%2C%20allowing%20NATO%20reinforcements%20early%20on.%20Which%20indicators%20would%20trigger%20such%20a%20response%20is%20classified.%20According%20to%20that%20logic%2C%20however%2C%20reinforcement%20would%20require%20political%20leaders%20to%20act%20before%20an%20attack%20has%20actually%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20are%20witnessing%20is%20the%20dissolution%20of%20NATO%2C%26quot%3B%20Anders%20Fogh%20Rasmussen%2C%20a%20former%20NATO%20secretary-general%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.welt.de%2Fpolitik%2Fausland%2Fplus69fd80d47e3ff373d429dc86%2Fanders-fogh-rasmussen-es-gibt-viel-zu-viel-friedensdenken.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Europe%20must%20rethink%20its%20defense%20plans%20and%20build%20the%20capabilities%20to%20act%20without%20waiting%20for%20Washington.%20Europe%20needs%20%26quot%3Bnew%20defense%20plans%20and%20new%20military%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20calculation%20is%20already%20shaping%20defense%20planning%20across%20NATO's%20eastern%20flank.%20Finland%20is%20making%20itself%20more%20difficult%20to%20invade.%20Poland%20is%20building%20up%20its%20military%20forces%2C%20fortifications%20and%20drone%20defense.%20And%20the%20Baltics%20are%20working%20to%20ensure%20they%20won't%20be%20left%20to%20fight%20on%20their%20own.%20Europe%20may%20not%20yet%20be%20ready%20to%20defend%20itself%20alone.%20But%20on%20its%20eastern%20frontier%2C%20it%20is%20already%20preparing%20for%20the%20day%20when%20it%20may%20have%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Finland%2C%20Col.%20Ari%20M%C3%A4%C3%A4tt%C3%A4%2C%20the%20Karelian%20brigade's%20deputy%20commander%2C%20was%20asked%20whether%2C%20with%20America's%20disengagement%2C%20NATO%20needs%20to%20become%20more%20European.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20a%20concern%20I%20have%20for%20my%20brigade%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20focus%20on%20military%20preparedness.%20Ask%20the%20politicians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELaura%20Kayali%2C%20Senior%20Defense%20Correspondent%20at%20POLITICO's%20Paris%20office%2C%20reported%20from%20Finland.%20Marcin%20Wyrwa%C5%82%2C%20a%20journalist%20with%20Onet%2C%20and%20Philipp%20Fritz%2C%20Warsaw%20Correspondent%20for%20WELT%2C%20reported%20from%20Poland.%20Carolina%20Dr%C3%BCten%2C%20International%20Security%20Correspondent%20at%20WELT%2C%20reported%20from%20Lithuania.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20harnesses%20the%20resources%20of%20the%20company's%20newsrooms%20to%20publish%20ambitious%20scoops%2C%20investigations%2C%20interviews%2C%20opinion%20pieces%20and%20analysis.%20It%20allows%20journalists%20%E2%80%94%20including%20those%20from%20POLITICO%2C%20Business%20Insider%2C%20WELT%2C%20BILD%2C%20Onet%20and%20Fakt%20%E2%80%94%20to%20collaborate%20on%20major%20stories%20for%20an%20international%20audience%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20across%20platforms%3A%20online%2C%20print%2C%20TV%20and%20audio.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-eastern-flank-prepares-to-fend-off-russia-without-us-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783238461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42d986e218c3b62535ef76%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-eastern-flank-prepares-to-fend-off-russia-without-us-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reporters%20traveled%20to%20three%20exposed%20stretches%20of%20Europe's%20eastern%20frontier%20and%20found%20varied%20strategies%20and%20uneven%20progress%20to%20deter%20Russia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Insider%20Inc.)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Beyonc%C3%A9%20surprises%20with%20long-unreleased%20song%20'Morning%20Dew%20(Donk)'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783238051000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-132192687%2Cimgsize-208611.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.co